<html>

<head>
<title>Union Summer Program Description</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h1 align=center>Program Description </h1>
<p>Union Summer is the AFL-CIO's new program to bring hundreds of young workers and college 
students into the streets and neighborhoods this summer to work on union organizing campaigns 
and political initiatives. </p>
<p>Union Summer sites will be located around the country. Our program will reach out to low wage 
and young workers, recent immigrants, women and people of color - the new face of labor. We 
will hit neighborhoods and work sites across the land with the message that all working people 
deserve dignity on the job and a living wage. In the face of today's profit-crazed corporations, we 
will win these things only if everyone stands up and demands them in a strong, unified voice. Union 
Summer will help thousands of workers find that voice. </p>
<p>Applicants accepted for Union Summer will be assigned to a three week placement on an 
organizing campaign or political project in June, July, or August. They will be responsible for 
transportation to their assigned sites. Once there, they will receive training, free housing, and a 
stipend of $210 per week. Take a stand for social justice. <em>Get involved in Union Summer!</em> </p>
<p align=center><a href="home.html">Union Summer Home</a> | <a href="answers.html">Q &amp; A</a><br>
<a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a></p>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; AFL-CIO</p>
</body>

</html>
