<head>
<title>Howto Organize</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<p align="center"><img src="images/orglogot.gif" align="bottom"
width="496" height="134"> </p>
<h2 align="center">How to start a union organizing campaign</h2>
<ul>
    <li>It is <b>your right</b> to support, form, and/or advocate
        a union at your workplace! </li>
    <li>In order to be recognized for collective bargaining, you
        must demonstrate to your employer that you represent a
        majority of the employees. This can be shown through an
        election or by checking signatures on petitions or cards. </li>
    <li>In order to assure you and your coworkers the best
        opportunity to win union recognition and a contract, you
        should contact the appropriate union to assist your
        efforts. </li>
    <li>If you are unsure of which union to contact, please fill
        out the <a href="respform.htm">response form</a>. Please
        email it to <i>organizers@aol.com</i> <b>or</b> send it
        via postal mail to the Organizing Institute at:<br>
        1101 14th Street NW<br>
        Suite 320 Washington, DC 20005.<br>
        Your information will be forwarded to organizers in your
        area.</li>
</ul>
<h3 align="center">For application call 1 (800)848-3021</h3>
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm">AFL-CIO Home Page</a> | <a
href="/orginst/index.htm">Organizing Institute Page</a></p>
