<html>
<head>
<title>Recruitment and Training</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body>
<p align="center"><img src="images/orglogot.gif" align="bottom"
width="496" height="134"> </p>
<h2 align="center">About the Recruitment and Training Program for
Union Organizers</h2>
<p><b>RESPONSIBILITIES:</b> Assist workers in gaining union
representation. Help to form a union among workers, such as
clerical, manufacturing, or healthcare workers. This requires
developing leadership, educating people about their rights,
explaining the union organizing process, and running a campaign
for union recognition. The most common reasons workers organize
unions today are to gain dignity, a voice on the job, and fair
treatment. </p>
<p><b>QUALIFICATIONS:</b> Commitment and dedication to building
the labor movement; energy and enthusiasm; leadership qualities;
communication skills; willingness to relocate; union, community,
or student organizing experience preferred. People of color,
bilingual applicants, and women are encouraged to apply. </p>
<p><b>STAGES OF THE TRAINING PROGRAM:</b> The Organizing
Institute Program includes a step by step process whereby
trainees gain increasing amounts of experience and
responsibility. The steps are the following: </p>
<dl>
    <dd>
        <h4>3-Day Training </h4>
    </dd>
    <dd>An intensive weekend course that teaches the basics of
        campaign strategy to potential organizers. Housing and
        food provided. </dd>
    <dd>
        <h4>Internship </h4>
    </dd>
    <dd>Selected applicants go on to a three-week field
        internship, where they learn the skills of union-
        building first hand. Includes $210/week stipend, housing,
        and transportation. </dd>
    <dd>
        <h4>Apprenticeship </h4>
    </dd>
    <dd>Apprentices are given greater responsibilities in
        campaigns and ongoing training for twelve weeks. Paid
        $400/week plus housing, transportation, and health
        insurance. </dd>
    <dd>
        <h4>Job Placement </h4>
    </dd>
    <dd>Apprentices who successfully complete the program are
        recommended by the Institute to be hired as Union
        Organizers by local and national unions. Placement rates
        for graduates have been over 90%. Starting pay ranges
        from $20,000 to $30,000. </dd>
</dl>
<hr>
<h4><a href="schedule.html">The Organizing Institute 3-Day
Training Schedule.</a></h4>
