<html>

<head>
<title>The AFL-CIO's LaborNET on CompuServe</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><img src="images/hmlogot.gif" align=bottom width=316 height=97></p>
<blockquote>
<p>LaborNET is an on-line communication network for trade unionists, offering users 
the opportunity to electronically access information from the national AFL-CIO 
and to exchange information with union activists throughout the country. </p>
<p>LaborNET is a private forum that resides on CompuServe, one of the nation's 
largest on-line services. </p>
<p>LaborNET includes four primary sections: a library, messages, announcements, and 
conferences. </p>
<blockquote>
<dl>
<dt><b>Library</b> </dt>
<dd>To many users, the library is LaborNET's most valuable 
component. Here you will find a wide range of public policy 
statements and other information. This repository of material 
includes everything from one-page fact sheets to detailed 
analyses of the latest AFL-CIO positions on key issues. </dd>
<dt><b>Messages</b> </dt>
<dd>The messages section is a place where members correspond 
with one another. Here you may find person-to-person 
notes, requests for information, answers to questions and 
continuing discussions. You can post your own messages, 
reply to others, or just read messages posted by other 
members. </dd>
<dt><b>Conference</b> </dt>
<dd>The conference section is where members can gather for 
&quot;live conversation.&quot; Here you may find several members 
engaged in a regularly scheduled meeting or participating in a 
special conference hosted by a guest speaker. </dd>
<dt><b>Announcements</b> </dt>
<dd>Announcements are used to inform members about changes 
in LaborNET. The scheduling of on-line conferences will be 
announced with this method. Information describing 
LaborNET and its components are also included here.</dd>
<dd><a href="flash.htm">Click here to review our current announcement</a></dd>
</dl>
</blockquote>
<p>Taken together, AFL-CIO LaborNET and CompuServe's Information Services 
are a wealth of information designed to keep union members up to date on labor 
issues. Participation costs $3 per month for unlimited access to AFL-CIO 
LaborNET and $9.95 for CompuServe's monthly service. </p>
<p><a href="lnreqst.htm">To receive further information about joining, click HERE.</a></p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>Copyright &#169; AFL-CIO<br>
</p>
</body>

</html>
