<head>
<title>Organizing: IBT flies with ValuJet, SEIU gains 3,000,
RWDSU wraps up unit, Coral Gables picks UNITE</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm" target="index.htm">AFL-CIO
Home Page</a> | <a href="/newsonline/news-archive.html">News
Archives</a> | <a href="/newsonline/newssearch.htm">Search News
Archives</a></p>
<p align="center"><strong><img src="../images/mastt.gif"
align="bottom"><br>
October 11, 1996</strong></p>
<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p align="center"><font size="4">Organizing: </font><a
        href="#IBT flies with ValuJet"><font size="4">IBT flies
        with ValuJet</font></a><font size="4">, </font><a
        href="#SEIU gains 3,000"><font size="4"><br>
        SEIU gains 3,000</font></a><font size="4">, </font><a
        href="#RWDSU wraps up unit "><font size="4">RWDSU wraps
        up unit</font></a><font size="4">,<br>
        </font><a href="#Coral Gables picks UNITE "><font
        size="4">Coral Gables picks UNITE</font></a></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p><a name="IBT flies with ValuJet">IBT flies with ValuJet</a> </p>
    <p>Mechanics at Atlanta-based ValuJet voted for Teamsters
    representation, with 42 of the eligible 70 workers casting
    their ballots in favor of the union. </p>
    <p>The mechanics wanted representation because of the
    company's subcontracting practices, which were blamed for
    maintenance problems and may have been responsible for a
    crash outside Miami this year that killed everyone on board. </p>
    <p>The Flight Attendants previously won the right to
    represent the attendants and have continued to press the
    carrier over the safety issue. ValuJet got clearance to
    resume operations in early October. </p>
    <p><a name="SEIU gains 3,000">SEIU gains 3,000</a> </p>
    <p>A unit of 3,000 Puerto Rican workers, members of the
    Sindicato Puertorriqueno de Trabajadores (SPT), has
    affiliated with the Service Employees. </p>
    <p>SEIU President Andy Stern made the announcement Oct. 8 in
    Puerto Rico, where he met with the health care and
    educational workers at various hospitals and schools who are
    members of UNTS, an SEIU affiliate. </p>
    <p><a name="RWDSU wraps up unit ">RWDSU wraps up unit </a></p>
    <p>Workers at Andrew Marc Outerwear Co. in Secaucus, N.J.,
    voted 23-5 for representation with the Retail, Wholesale and
    Department Store Union. </p>
    <p>The key issue for the predominately Hispanic workers was
    discrimination in wages. When workers approached management
    to ask for a raise, they were given two alternatives -- get
    back to work or get out. </p>
    <p>&quot;They knew they had another alternative,&quot; said
    RWDSU Secretary-Treasurer Stuart Appelbaum. &quot;They
    contacted the union.&quot; </p>
    <p><a name="Coral Gables picks UNITE ">Coral Gables picks
    UNITE </a></p>
    <p>Workers at Coral Gables Convalescent Center in Miami voted
    31- 20 for UNITE representation. </p>
    <p>&quot;It's a simple matter of respect. That's what we
    want, and that's what we voted for today,&quot; said Prima
    Washington, a 20- veteran at the center. </p>
</blockquote>
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm" target="index.htm">AFL-CIO
Home Page</a> | <a href="/newsonline/news-archive.html">News
Archives</a> | <a href="/newsonline/newssearch.htm">Search News
Archives</a></p>
