<title>UAW writers win top ILCA awards</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm" target="index.htm">AFL-CIO
Home Page</a> | <a href="/newsonline/news-archive.html">News
Archives</a> | <a href="/newsonline/newssearch.htm">Search News
Archives</a></p>
<p align="center"><strong><img src="../images/aflnews.gif"
align="bottom" width="443" height="140"><br>
September 20, 1996</strong></p>
<blockquote>
    <p align="center"><font size="4"><strong>UAW writers win top
    ILCA awards </strong></font></p>
    <p>Two writers for UAW Solidarity have garnered top honors in
    the 1996 ILCA journalism contest. </p>
    <p>David Elsila and Andrew Neather, who collaborated on
    &quot;Putting Together the Affirmative Action Puzzle,&quot;
    received the Max Steinbock Award, which honors outstanding
    individual effort in exploring an issue of concern to working
    families that displays particular sensitivity and insight
    into the human spirit. </p>
    <p>Receiving honorable mentions for the Steinbock Award were
    Bill Hillman of the Television and Radio Artists for the
    article &quot;Blacklist,&quot; and Nancy Brigham, also
    writing in Solidarity, for the article &quot;What Will Happen
    to the Children? -- How `Welfare Reform' Will Hurt Those
    Least Able to Defend Themselves.&quot; </p>
    <p>The Saul Miller Awards recognize outstanding efforts by
    the labor press in presenting stories about union organizing
    and victories. </p>
    <p>UFCW ACTION was given the award of excellence for
    international union publications, with the Service Employees'
    UNION winning second place and UFCW Canada Action and IUE
    News winning third place. </p>
    <p>Top local union publications were UFCW Local 400's Union
    Leader, followed by AFT Local 5047's Update 47 and
    Machinists' Local Lodge 141's The Transporter. </p>
    <p>The top awards are: </p>
    <p>SAUL MILLER AWARDS </p>
    <p>Best Story, Series, Editorial or Column </p>
    <p>Local Union Publications -- The Transporter, IAM Local
    Lodge 141, Novi, Mich.; Union Leader, UFCW Local 400,
    Landover, Md.; CWA Today, Communications Workers Local 3204,
    Atlanta. </p>
    <p>All Other Publications -- Solidarity, UAW, Detroit; UFCW
    Action, Food and Commercial Workers, Washington; Public
    Employee Press, AFSCME District Council 37, New York; The MFT
    Federation Paper, Massachusetts Federation of Teachers,
    Boston. </p>
    <p>Best Use of Graphics </p>
    <p>Local Union Publications -- The Voice of Local 880, UFCW
    Local 880, Cleveland; 509 News, SEIU Local 509, Cambridge,
    Mass. </p>
    <p>All Other Publications -- UNION, SEIU, Washington; IAM
    Journal, Machinists, Upper Marlboro, Md.; California AFL-CIO
    News, California Labor Federation, San Francisco. </p>
    <p>Unique Performance </p>
    <p>Local Union Publications -- No awards. </p>
    <p>All Other Publications -- IAM Journal, IAM. </p>
    <p>Non-periodical, Special Publications </p>
    <p>Editorial Excellence </p>
    <p>Local Union Publications -- No awards. </p>
    <p>All Other Publications -- Minnesota AFL-CIO Viewpoint, </p>
    <p>Minnesota AFL-CIO, St. Paul, Minn.; Public Employee Press,
    AFSCME DC 37; The Laborer, Laborers, Washington. </p>
    <p>Best Use Of Graphics </p>
    <p>Local Union Publications -- Movers &amp; Shakers, AFSCME
    Local 1549, New York. </p>
    <p>All Other Publications -- The Laborer, LIUNA; Public
    Employee Press, AFSCME DC 37. </p>
    <p>GENERAL EXCELLENCE AWARDS </p>
    <p>International And National Union Publications </p>
