<head>
<title>Just in time for Labor Day</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><a href="/index.htm" target="index.htm">AFL-CIO
Home Page</a> | <a href="/newsonline/news-archive.html">News
Archives</a> | <a href="/newsonline/newssearch.htm">Search News
Archives</a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="../images/aflnews.gif" align="bottom"
width="443" height="140"></p>
<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <blockquote>
            <blockquote>
                <p align="center"><strong>August 23, 1996</strong></p>
            </blockquote>
        </blockquote>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
    <p align="center"><font size="4"><strong>Just in Time for
    Labor Day </strong></font></p>
    <p align="left"><font size="4"><br>
    </font>AFL-CIO President John J. Sweeney has written a new
    book about the fight for economic security and social
    justice. </p>
    <p>&quot;America Needs A Raise,&quot; published by Houghton
    Mifflin, is an honest, easy-to-read explanation of how
    corporations and government have failed America's working
    families &thorn; and what we can do about it. </p>
    <p>The book sketches Sweeney's rise from humble jobs in the
    Bronx, N.Y., to the leadership of the U.S. labor movement.
    Along the way, he developed a sense that workers have to
    stick together to build communities that nourish families and
    reward hard work. </p>
    <p>His analysis of what has gone wrong in America is well
    documented, with facts and figures that testify to why
    &quot;America Needs A Raise.&quot; </p>
    <p>Sale proceeds will go to a special fund to help working
    Americans organize for higher living standards. You can find
    the book at your local book store. For more information, call
    the AFL- CIO Publications Division at 202-637-5010. </p>
</blockquote>
