<TITLE>Department of Water Resources and Harbour Engineering</TITLE>
<H3>  The Department of Water Resources and Harbour Engineering </H3>
<HR><UL>The Department was founded in 1935. Having developed over such a long time , it has an aboundant faculty, and fairly advanced teaching facilities. There are two attached research institutes of Hydraulic Engineering and Water Transportation Engineering Company.<BR>
The graduates of the department are flexible and adaptable to a variety of work. They are capable of survey, design, construction and management work, as well as research in the fields of harbor, hydraulic and civil engineering.  
</UL><HR>




</DOC>
