 Materials for separation with function of steric and molecular recognition .<BR>
 Column packing material for HPLC. New type of ion exchanger. <BR>
 Materials for gas separation <BR>
 <BR>
 2)Polymeric biomaterials for medical practice<BR>
 Materials for blood-cleaning<BR>
 Materials with activity of immunity <BR>
 Biomimetic polymers<BR>
 Nanoparticle biomaterials and new drug-delivery systems Immobilized Enzymes Biocompartible polymers and artificial organs <BR>
 <BR>
 3)Reactive polymers <BR>
 Acid and base catalysts with high temperature resistance<BR>
 Marcomolecular metallic complex catalysts <BR>
 Polymeric catalysts for enantio synthesis Solid-phase synthesis of bioactive substances <BR>
 <BR>
 4)Correlation of properties with marco and microstructures of functional polymer materials Chain motion state of crosslinking polymers <BR>
 Crosslinking network morphology of polymers <BR>
 Distribution of function groups on polymer chains or network of crosslinking polymers<BR>
 Pore structure of crosslinked polymer at operating environment <BR>
 Characterization methods of structure and performance of crosslinked polymers <BR>
