<TITLE>STATE KEY LABORATORY FOR NOVEL SOFTWARE TECHNOLOGY </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>STATE KEY LABORATORY FOR NOVEL SOFTWARE TECHNOLOGY </H2>
<P><U><B> </B>
<H4></H4>
<UL>
<LI>Nanjing University 
</UL>
<P></U>
<H3>Director of Lab: <B>Prof. Lu Jian</B><BR>
 Chairman of Academic Committee: <B>Prof. Sun Zhongxiu</B><BR>
 Honorary Director of Lab: Prof. Xu Jiafu</H3>
<P>
<HR>
<P><B>Main Research Fields: </B>
<P>Software automation, distributed computing, new-style programming, intelligent operating system and software development environment. 
<HR>
<P><B>1. Director of Lab </B><BR>
 Prof. Lu jian He received his Bs, Ms, and Ph. D. in Nanjing University in 1981, 1984, 1988 respectively. His research interest is software automation. He has published 20 or more paper on the journals Science in china, University Computing, etc. <BR>
 Tel: 025-6634651-3283 <BR>
 Email:postcomp@nju. edu. cn <BR>
 Honorary Director of lab<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Xu Jiafu</B><BR>
 His main research interests are high level programming languages, novel programming, software automation. He has published 115 papers and 5 books. He is also awarded six times the national awards(first level). <BR>
 Tel: 025-6634651-3283 <BR>
 Email:postcomp@nju. edu. cn<BR>
 <B>2. Chairman of Academic </B><BR>
 Committee Prof. Sun Zhongxiu His main research interests include distributed computing, operating system, and intelligent operating systems. He has published more than 100 papers and 4 books. <BR>
 Tel: 025-6634651-2339 <BR>
 Email:postcom@nju. edu. cn <BR>
 <BR>
 3. <B>Main Research Scholars </B><BR>
 <B>Prof. Xie Li </B><BR>
 His research interests are operating systems, distributed computing, and intelligent operating systems. He has published more tan 80 papers and four books. <BR>
 <B>Prof. Zheng Guoliang</B><BR>
 His research interests are programming languages, compiling techniques, software engineering, and software developments. He has published 50 or more papers and four books. <BR>
 <B>Assoc. Prof. Zhu Hong </B><BR>
 He received Ph. D. in Nanjing University in 1987. His research interests are software automation. He has published more than 30 papers in science in China, University Computing, Software Engineering Journal, etc. <BR>
 <B>Assoc. Prof. YiBo </B><BR>
 He received Ph. D. in Nanjing University in 1990. His research interests are software automation and computer architecture. He has published nearly 20 papers in Science in Chain, Theoretical Computer Science, Journal of Symbolic Computation, etc. <BR>
 <B>Assoc. Prof. Du Xing </B><BR>
 He received his Ph. D. in Nanjing University in 1991. His research interests are distributed computing, human computer interaction, computer supported cooperative work(CSCW). He has published more than 30 papers in Science in China, Software Engineering Journal, Engineering Applications of Artificial Intelligence, etc. 
<HR>
<H3>Equipment</H3>
<P>This lab equipment with a set of VAX 8530 computer system and seven SUN workstation(two SUN-4 and five SUN-3)connected in Ethernct. The former is a world-wide popular computer system with 4 MIPS CPU, 32 GB main memory. 2500GB disk. and many system software like VMS and ULTRIX operating system, FORTRAN, COBOL, C, PASCAL, PL/1, BASIC, PROLOG and LISP languages, graphical software, and UNIFY, ORACLE databases. It has been put into use since 1980 and opens 355 days a years. Up to now, more than fifty projects have been completed on it. SUN workstations are well suitable for software research and development. They have been used frequently for high-tech, the national research and the national science foundation projects, etc. and play an important role in graduate student education. 
<HR>
<H3>Research Directions</H3>
<P>Computer Software has been developed rapidly for more than thirty years. but its current states is far from satisfaction. The three problems for software are weak functionality, poor quality and low productivity. Since software is essentially an intelligent-intensive product, it is of vital importance to conduct research on software development techniques. <BR>
 This lab mainly studies the so-called &quot;novel&quot;computer software techniques characterized by the following features: intelligence, automation, integration and naturalization. <BR>
 The intelligence technology is aimed at making software products of intelligence, the automation technology at realizing the automation of software development process, the integration technology at providing means of composition from software pieces, the parallelism technology at enhancing processing speed, and the naturalization technology at improving user friendliness in man-machine interfaces, description languages and software systems, thus allowing the users to have an easy access to software and computer systems. <BR>
 Based on the above understanding and our existing research work, this lab has taken software automation, distributed computing, new-style programming, intelligent operating systems and software development environment to be its research directions. <BR>
 The short-term goal of software automation is to improve the practicality of existing systems and to focus on machine learning, Chinese understanding and related theoretical foundations for the sakes of constructing new software systems. The long-term goal is to propose a new development paradigm and its corresponding model realizing the automatic generation from requirements definitions to executable programs. <BR>
 The short-term goal of distributed computing is to focus on the configuration of distributed operating systems, task allocation, synchronization mechanisms, distributed databases, etc. , the long-term goal is to propose some new theory of distributed computing and implement more practical systems. <BR>
 The short-term goal of new-style programming is to design a knowledge representation language, to design and implement languages for design, functionality and requirements descriptions, and to study suitable knowledge processing computer architectures. The long-term goal is to design and implement a new-style computer system and its programming system. <BR>
 The short-term goal of intelligent operating systems is to study the characteristics and structure of intelligent operating systems, intelligent resource allocation algorithms and intelligent man-machine interfaces, etc. . and to implement a practical system. The long-term goal is to implement different kinds of operating systems for intelligent computes and to break through some related theoretical problems. <BR>
 The short-term goal of software development environment is to develop a practical computer-aided software engineering system and a software development apprentice. The long-term goal is to implement an intelligent software development environment and to complete some theoretical research work correspondingly. 
<HR>
<H3>Research work </H3>
<P>Thirty-seven research projects have been carried out since the lab began its construction. Among them, seven are belonging to the national high-tech research projects, fourteen the national research and development projects, five the national science foundation projects, six provincial projects and five projects from other supports. Up to now, twenty-three projects have been fulfilled, of which fifteen passed the technical identification and five were awarded. more than two hundred papers have been published in the national and international academic journal and five books have been published, too. The details are given below. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Software Automation</B><BR>
 Five experimental systems have been completed. The NDAUTO system is based on the self-designed software specification language GSPEC. It automatically or semi-automatically transforms software specifications to PASCAL codes by the use of the combination of transformational and procedural approaches. It has been operational on IBM PC/AT microcomputer and SUN workstations since 1987. The NDTPS system is a transformational programming system based on the self-designed meta language TrapML. It is oriented to multiple object languages and multiple transformation strategies. It was implemented on IBM PC/AT in 1987. The NDADAS system is based on an improved software specification language FGSPEC. It combines the deductive and transformational approaches and heuristically(if necessary)generates software design specification from its functional ones. It was accomplished on SUN workstations in 1998. The NDIPS system is an inductive software automation system. It accepts program hypothesis validation routines. It adopts the partial ordering structure of a generalized subsumption relation, an automation model interface algorithm And program hypothesis validation routines. It was implemented on SUN workstations in 1989. The NDSAIL system is a software automation system with self-learning ability. It is based on the EBL method and some new techniques are development by the system designers. It is operational in SUN workstations in 1991. In addition to the above systems, some valuable results have also been obtained on the correctness of software specifications, software development frame, and analogical inference. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Disributed Computing </B><BR>
 Based on the ZCZ, ZH and SN distributed computing systems accomplished five years ago, other four systems have also been finished. EGLI is a distributed data processing system using local network technology. It implements the active communication and network file transition technology in the distributed Chinese database management system DdBASE-2, the connection between local network and remote workstations, tools for Chinese electronic mails, etc. and more than ten different kinds of applications software for the purpose of office automation, etc. It was fulfilled in 1986. ZGL is a heterogeneous distributed operating system running in 16-bit microcomputers network environment using Ethernet, ominet and RS232C connections. It was completed in 1989. Unify is a Chinese and English compatible distributed database management system based on SUN Unify and running on SUN workstations connected in Ethernet. It is upward compatible and was implemented in 1989. ZGL3 is a distributed operating system for different kinds of machines including 16-bit (IBM PC compatible) computer and 32-bit (SUN workstations compatible) microcomputers connected in Ethernet. It supports original functionality of MS-DOS and Unix and provides file sharing, processor sharing, process communication, distributed file systems, distributed programming language C , and electronic mails. It was accomplished in 1990. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>New-Style Programming </B><BR>
 A data-driven multi-stack reduction machine model FPMND and its FP programming system were fulfilled by the end of 1984. This model consisted of a host machine (a M16 microcomputer) and three processing elements(single-board computer). An experimental parallel inference system NDPIS was also accomplished in 1986. It was based on self-designed kernel language KLND and made use of the &quot;substitution-driven&quot;concept. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Intelligence Operating Systems </B><BR>
 <BR>
 Three experimental systems have developed. The intelligent operating system KZL was completed in 1989 which aimed at improving man-machine communication ability. It consists of a communication expert system, a knowledge-based management system KZL/ZG and an Ethernet distributed operating system EOS. It provides Chinese understanding, on-line inquerring, on-line learning and voice input, etc. The general-purpose natural language interface KZ2/TZJ adopts a hierarchical method independent of application domains and allows the users to manipulate computers in Chinese conveniently. It is extensible and can be treated as a common national language interface for various operating systems like UNIX, VMS and MS-DOS, etc. It was implemented in 1990 including some learning ability also. The knowledge-based operating system KZ10 consists of an intelligent man-machine interface(KZ10/JK) and a knowledge-based distributed task scheduling system(KZ10/RD). The former provides the users with a friendly operating system interface to express their requirements through different input means. The latter implements an intelligent distributed task scheduling and a knowledge processing unit to make the system to be self-adaptable and self-learnable. it was fulfilled in 1990. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Software Development Environment </B><BR>
 Ten systems have been developed up to now. A syntax-directed editor was completed in 1986 to avoid syntactical errors for multiple languages. It is convenient to novices. The MODULA-2 compiler validation system constructs a testing package at first and then produces a validation report after the test. It was also accomplished in 1986. The PDL/M2 system completed in 1987 interactively transforms PDL(self-designed language)programs to MODULA-2 ones. The programming apprentice system NPA completed in 1990 is used to assist programmers in algorithm design. A testing tool system for testing programs in MODULA-2 and C was also fulfilled in 1990. A transformational system completed in 1990 consists of three subsystems to transform programs in COBOL, MODULA-2 and PASCAL to the corresponding in C . The requirements analysis tool completed in 1988 is used in structured analysis and structured design. A multi-lingual software understanding tool SUIE and an IBM assembly language transformation and understanding system wee also developed in 1990. The former is an integrated toolset system on SUN workstations to analyze software structures for multiple languages. The latter is rule-based integrated system. 
<HR>
<P><B>Software Automation </B><BR>
<B> </B><B>1</B>. A Knowldge-Based Approach to program Synthesis from Examples Zhu Hong, Jin Lingzi Journal of computer Science and Technology, Vol. 6. NO. 1, 1991, pp. 47-58<BR>
 <B>2</B>. Program Transformation by Solving Equations Zhu Hong Journal of Computer Science and Technology, Vol. 6 No. 2, 1991, pp. 167-177 29. 29. Framework of Algorithms Correctness in NDADAS Lu Jian Science in China (Series A), Vol. 34, No. 7, 1991, PP. 875-884<BR>
