<TITLE>STATE KEY LABORATORY OF POWDER METALLURGY </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>STATE KEY LABORATORY OF POWDER METALLURGY </H2>
<P><U>
<UL>
<LI>
</UL>
<P></U>
<H3>Director of Lab: <B>Prof.Huang Boyun </B><BR>
 Chairman of Academic Committee: <B>Prof.Huang Peiyun </B></H3>
<HR>
<H4>1. An Brief Introduction of Director of the Lab</H4>
<P><B>Huang Baiyun</B>, male, Prof., was born in Nan County, Hunan Province in 1945, was graduated from central South Institute of Mining and Metallurgy (CSIMM) in 1969, and studied in U.S.A for eight years and earned doctor degree. As the former chief engineer and the chairman of Powder Metallurgy Research Institute in the CSUT, now he is the vice president of CSUT, the director of the State Key Laboratory for Powder Metallurgy, the permanent member of the Sinica Material Research Committee and the Sinica Non-ferrous metal Society, the member of the 863 hi-tech expert committee. He was chosen as a state outstanding expert and was elected one of the &quot;100 national excellent public servants&quot; in 1994.<BR>
 <BR>
 His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main fields are TiAl-based high temperature alloy and biological ceramics.<BR>
 <BR>
 Tel:(0731)8879838 (home) (0731)-8879224 
<H4>2. The Director of the Academic Committee</H4>
<H4></H4>
<P><B>Pro. Huang Peiyun</B>, male, academician of the Sinica Academy of Engineering, was born in Fuzhou, Fujian Province in 1917. In 1935, he was graduated from Tsinghua University, and in 1945 earned a Sc. D. MIT. USA. He was the dean of Mining and Metallurgy Department in Wuhan University, vice president of CSIMM, and the chairman of the P/M Research Institute in CSUT. At present, he is the academic advisor and the chairman or academic committee of CSUT, (He is the founder of the Powder Metallurgy discipline in CUST and in China),the permanent member of Sinica Metal Society and Sinica Non-ferrous Metal Society, and emeritus chairman of Science and Technology Association in Hunan.<BR>
 <BR>
 His professional subjects are powder metallurgy, metallurgical physical chemistry and metal material. His main field is basic theory of powder metallurgy.<BR>
 <BR>
 Tel:(0731)-8879565 (home) 
<H4>3. The Brief Introduction of the Key Staff</H4>
<H4></H4>
<P><B>Prof. Lu Haibo</B>, male, was born in Jiujiang of Jianxi Province in 1931, was graduated from CSIMM in 1956. He was the standing vice-chairman of P/M Research Institute in CUST. At present he is the vice-chairman of Sinica Non-ferrous metal powder metallurgy and metal Ceramic Society. His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main fields are hard alloy and special powder preparing.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Zuo zhiqiang</B>, male, was born in Linchuan of Jianxi Province in 1936, was graduated from CSIMM in 1960. In 1979, he was sent to study in Sweden. He has held the position of vice-chairman of the P/M Research Institute, and at present, he is the chief engineer, standing vice-director of the state key laboratory for P/M and one of the editors of the &quot;inter. J.RM &amp;HM&quot;. His professional subjects are metal material and powder metallurgy. His main fields are refractory metal and hard material. He is also a state outstanding expert.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Wang Linsen</B>, born in Xingjiang County of Hunan Province in 1938, was graduated from CSIMM in 1960. He was one of the vice- chairman of P/M Research Institute. His professional subjects are press work and powder metallurgy, and his main fields are composites and special ceramics.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Qu Xianhui</B>, born in Li County of Hunan Province, was graduated from CSIMM in 1981, and studied in Canada from 1986 to 1988. He earned doctor degree. At present he is the assistant of chairman of P/M Research Institute. His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main field is TiAl-based high temperature materials.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Yao Dechao</B>, born in Xiabhua of Hunan Province in 1936, was graduated from CSIMM in 1960. He is one of the vice-chairman of P/M Research Institute. His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main fields are sintered steel and P/M heat resisting alumina alloy.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Li Xibing</B>, born in Shaoyang of Hunan Province in 1939, was graduated from CSIMM in 1983. He is one of the vice-chairman of P/M Research Institute now. His professional subject is power metallurgy, and his main fields are antifriction material and self-lubricating material.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Prof. Cheng Kanghua</B>, born in Ningbo, Zhejiang Province in 1962, was graduated from CSIMM in 1982. He earned doctor degree in 1991 and worked as post-doctor in North-east University (Dongbai University).He is the secretary of Prof. Huang Peiyun. His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main fields are high-temperature superconductive material and carbon fiber composite material.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Asso. Prof. He Anan</B>, born in Yiyang, Hunan Province in 1949, was graduated from CSIMM in 1970, and in 1985 he earned doctor degree. He studied in England in 1989. His professional subject is powder metallurgy, and his main fields are CAD on material and friction material.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Asso. Prof. Zhang Shugao</B>, born in Xianyin, Hunan Province, was graduated from Hunan University in 1981, and 1990 he earned doctor degree. His professional subject is inorganic non-metal material and and his main field is functional ceramics<BR>
 .<BR>
 <B>Asso. Prof. Weng Liuqian</B>, born in Changsha in 1962, was graduated from TsingHua University and earned master degree of Sinica Science Academy in 1989. He is studying in England. His professional subject is material science and his main fields are fine ceramics and functional ceramics.<BR>
 
<HR>
