<HR>
<P>5. <B>The Brief Introduction of the Research Direction and Scientific Research Programs of the Laboratory </B>
<OL>
<LI><STRONG>The Main Research Direction and Signification of the Laboratory </STRONG><BR>
 The research direction of this laboratory is powder metallurgy and powder science including the basic theory of P/M, P/M technology and P/M material science. Advanced research programs in the fields of P/M material science and engineering are undertaken and high-level qualified scientists and technicians are trained in this laboratory. The main research directions and their significance are listed as following.<BR>
 <BR>
 <SAMP>a. </SAMP>The Theory and New Technology for Powder Manufacturing; Rapid solidification technology, the manufacturing of the superfine, noncrystal, qualicrystal and microcrystal powder, the preparing of the composite powder and the powder which have specific shape, self- propagating high temperature synthesis technology, powder property testing.<BR>
 <BR>
 <SAMP>b.</SAMP> Structure and Property of the P/M Material Strengthening and toughening of the P/M material, phase interface characteristics and materials property, nonequalibrium thermodynamics and phase transformation dynamics.<BR>
 <BR>
 <SAMP>c. </SAMP>Newly Developed P/M Material with High Property Refractory metals and compounds, carbides and superhard material, friction material and friction-reducing material, sintering steel, P/M nonferrous alloy, catalyst material, porous material, metal ceramics, structural cetamics, functional ceramics, magnetic material, bio- ceramics, composites, material aided designing with computer.<BR>
 <BR>
 <SAMP>d.</SAMP> Theory and Technology for Forming Froming theory, hot pressing, cold and hot isostatic pressing, powder injection moulding and extrusion moulding, powder swaged forging, hot extrusion, spray moulding and explosion concertions.<BR>
 <BR>
 <SAMP>e. </SAMP>Theory and Technology of Sintering Solid phrase sintering, liquid phrase sintering, reaction sintering, activation sintering, theory and technology of compacting.<BR>
 <BR>
 P/M is the edge discipline between metallurgy and materials science. It is also one of the materials fields which developed very rapidly at the present time. P/M methods not only remain and develop its original advantages, such as low cost, economy n energy, controllability of the porosity, ease to the achieve the composition between metal and nonmetal or metal and polymer, but also have been developed as an effective method to manufacture all kinds of high level property structural materials, specially functional material and materials which work at limit condition. P/M technology has become the frontier fields of modern material science and advanced technological development. The establishment of the main research direction for this laboratory is based on strategic consideration for economic development and defense necessity. <BR>
 
<LI><B>The Contents of the Research Work</B><BR>
 During the period of the construction, P/M discipline have undertaken three &quot;863&quot; projects, eight &quot;the eighth five-year plan&quot; projects, four projects of &quot;national the eighth five-year plan in military&quot; and sixteen projects of all kinds national funds programs, all the above projects have fulfilled satisfactory or finished according to the planned speed. In resent years the construction of the state laboratory especially by the importing and running of the some advanced key equipment. A favorable circulation between construction and development has been achieved.<BR>
 <BR>
 The research work include the following items since 1991: <BR>
 <STRONG>1)The Manufacturing of the Special Powder</STRONG> <BR>
 The work have been done including: the production of the noncrystal, qualicrystal and microcrystal metal powder through rapid solidification technology, the production of the superfine tungsten powder through the acetamide tungstate method, the production of superfine ceramics powder using sol-gel method, the production of the clad composite powder using sol-salt method, the production of the refraction compounds composite powder using self-propagating high temperature synthesis technology, the production of the thermal spraying powder used for aerospacecraft through spray method, and so on.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>2)The Study of the New P/M Technology</B> <BR>
 The work have been done including: the study of the impact spray- rapid solidification technology, the investigation on the production of the carbides printing needle using powder extrution moulding, the developing of the new technology equipment used for sinter/hot isostatic pressing, the investigation on the dense law about powder HIP and sinter/HIP, the study of law about powder spray moulding. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>3)The Study of the New P/M Material</B> <BR>
 The work have been done since 1991 including the development of the new aerospace friction material, the development of the AIN ceramics, the study of the bioceramics, the study of the high temperature self- lubriction thrust bearing, the development of the superfine carbides, the study on the TiAl intermetallic compounds, the friction material for automobile, the development of the large expansion coefficient heavy alloy, the development of pivot material using for aerospace devices, the development of the new heat resistance Aluminum alloy and so on. <BR>
 <BR>
 4)<B>The Study of the P/M Testing Method </B><BR>
 The work have been done including: the study of the standardization about the grading of submicrometre and superfine powder, the study of new technology testing thermal conductivity properties, the study of high temperature X-ray diffraction technology.<BR>
 <BR>
 5) <B>The Study of the P/M Theory</B><BR>
 The work have been done including: the theory about powder moulding and sintering, the study of the interface state and property of composites, phrase diagram computation, material design aided by computer. <BR>
 
</OL>
<UL>
<LI><B>Achievements since 1991</B><BR>
 Since 1991, the items of research subjects and the amount of the research funds have been increasing steady, which were burdened by the key laboratory.<BR>
 In 1991, the items of research subjects are 33, the amount of research funds is RMB 2.04 million yuan.<BR>
 In 1992, the items of research subjects are 39, the amount of research funds is RMB 2.29 million yuan. <BR>
 In 1993, the items of research subjects are 46, the amount of research funds is RMB 3.52 million yuan. <BR>
 In 1994, the items of research subjects are 38, the amount of research funds is RMB 3.7 million yuan. <BR>
 In 1995, the items of research subjects are 52, till June, the amount of research funds is RMB 2.8 million yuan. <BR>
 There are 4 research achievement past through the department or province appraisal in 1992, among which 1 fist state prize, 1 first department prize, 2 second department prize. In 1993, 6 research achievement passed through the appraisal, 1 first department prize, 2 second department prize.<BR>
 In 1994, 5 research achievement passed through the appraisal, 2 first department prize, 1 third prize, 1 fourth prize. <BR>
 Since 1991, the key laboratory has obtained 12 patents. The situation of issued articles written by the research of the researchers of the laboratory os showed as followed.<BR>
 <BR>
 Year: 1992; Total: 93; Important Journal:25 <BR>
Year: 1993; Total: 110; Important Journal:31 <BR>
Year: 1994; Total: 160; Important Journal:44 <BR>
Year: 1995; Total: &gt;200; <BR>
The important journals means the first academic journal, international academic journal and international academic conference symposium.<BR>
 The key laboratory organized the 1994 National Powder Metallurgy Academic Meeting, edited the conference symposium. Three sepcialistic books have been published: Special Ceramics, Powder Metallurgy Testing Techniques, Powder Metallurgy Electric Furnace. 
</UL>
