<TITLE>STATE KEY LABORATORY OF BROADBAND OPTICAL FIBER TRANSMISSION AND COMMUNICATION SYSTEM </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>STATE KEY LABORATORY OF BROADBAND OPTICAL FIBER TRANSMISSION AND COMMUNICATION NETWORKS<U><B> </B></H2>
<H4></H4>
<UL>
<LI>University of Electronic Science and Technology of China 
</UL>
<P></U>
<H3>Director of Lab: <B>Prof. Lu Rongxing </B><BR>
 Chairman of Academic Committee: <B>Prof. Li Lemin</B></H3>
<HR>
<P><B>Main Research Fields</B>: 
<OL>
<LI>Broadband optical fiber transmission theory and technology. 
<LI>Broadband optical fiber transmission systems and communication networks.Sun 
</OL>
<HR>
<P><B>Director of Lab: </B><B><BR>
</B> <B>Prof. Lu Rongxing</B> was born in Wuxi, Jiangsu province on March 7,1939. He graduated from Radio-physics Department of Chengdu Institute of Radio Engineering in 1962. since 1962, He has been teaching and researching in the university. His research ranges from infrared technology, Laser technology, Optical communication to Integrated optics. He has published paper 25 in this area. He was a vice-chairman of Optoelectronic Department, deputy-director of Science Research Office, and director of Foreign Affairs Office in 1984,1987 and 1991 respectively. He promoted a professor in 1992. Now he is the director of State Key Lab of Broadband Optical Transmission and Communication Networks. He is a member of council of Chinese Institute of Electronics. <BR>
 Tel: 86-28-3201024<BR>
 E_mail: rxlu@uestc\:edu.cn<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Chairman of Academic Committee: </B><B><BR>
</B> <B>Prof. Lin Weigan </B>was born in Zhejiang province, china, on May 28 1932. He graduated from Jiao tong University, Shanghai, China, in 1952. Majoring in electrical engineering. From 1980_1982, he was a visiting scholar at University of California, San Diego, USA His research work has been in the area of digital information transmission and communication networks including broadband communication and ATM networks. He has published more than 110 papers and 2 books. hHe was awarded more than ten terms of national, provincial and ministry prize for research and development. He is a fellow of CIC.<BR>
 Tel: 86-28-3202343 
<P><B>Major Young Researchers:</B><B><BR>
</B> <BR>
 <B>Assoc.Prof. Sun Hairong </B>was born in 1968 in Shanghai. He obtained B.S. and M.S. degree in Electronic Engineering from Shanghai Jiaotong University in 1988 and 1991 respectively. He received the Ph.D. degree from University of Electronic Science and Technology of China in 1993. Since than, he joined the State Key Lab. His main interest is communication network theory, he has published about 40 papers and one book. <BR>
 <B>Assoc.Prof. Luo Xiaobing</B><BR>
 <B>Prof. Qiu Kun </B>was born in August, 1964. He received B.S. degree from Chengdu Institute of Radio Engineering 1985, and M.S., Ph.D. degree from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 1987 and 1990 respectively. After graduation, he has been researching and teach in the State Key Lab of UEST, as a lecturer in 1990, an associate professor in 1992, and a professor in 1995. Now he is the deputy director of the State Key Lab. His present research interest includes ultrafast optoelectronics, fiber amplifiers, SCM optical fiber transmission system and integrated service CATV networks.He has published more than 40 papers and one book. He is a member of IEEE, and a senior member of CIE. <BR>
 <B>Hu li </B>was born in Guangan, Sichuan on July 15,1994. He was Graduated from the Chengdu Institute of Radio Engineering in 1967, and received M.S. degree in same university in 1981. He was a visiting scholar at Tokyo University during 1985_1986. He was promoted an associate professor and a professor in 1987 and 1993 respectively in UEST. His main interest includes optical fiber transmission theory, interaction between light wave and microwave. He has published about 40 papers. He was awarded 3 provincial and ministry prize.<BR>
 <B>Mei Kejun</B>, was born in Chengdu, China, in September 1938. He graduated from the Chengdu Institute of Radio Engineering(now UEST).Since 1972, he has been teaching and researching on optoelectronics and optical fiber communication technology. In 1990, he joined the State Key Lab as the chief of the 2-nd division and he promoted as a professor in 1992. His present interests include high speed modulation and measurements of semiconductor laser diodes, high speed optical fiber CATV systems, optical fiber distribution/access networks, WDM and EDFA technology, and optical fiber area networks. He has published 40 papers and was awarded 4 prizes. <BR>
 <B>Tang Mingguang</B>, was born in 1937. He graduated from Chengdu Institute of Radio Engineering in 1960. During 1981-1984, he was a visiting scholar in Polytechnic of New York, USA he promoted a professor in 1988. During 1990-1994, he was the deputy director of the State Key Lab. His main research area includes optical communication, optical fiber sensors, and ultrafast optoelectronics. He has published 70 papers, and 3 books. He was awarded 1 national invention prize, 3 Provincial and ministry prizes, and 1 patent. He is the member of IEEE, and a fellow of CIC. <BR>
 
<HR>
<H3>Introduction of Major Equipment </H3>
<P><B>HP-712-60 and HP-715-64 Workstation</B>, Time of Delivery: April, 1993. The workstation have total RAM Space 65536kbyte, within which 59068kbyte are usable. Peripheral equipment are follows: Plotter, Laser Jetter, Tape driver, CD-Drive etc. the workstation equipped with CAD Software provided by Mentor is mainly used in CAD of logic circuits. It also can be used for numeric calculation, and computer simulation, so that, we have also brought software of FORTRAN, C, and PASCAL.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>TEK-DSA602A</B>, Digital Signal Analyser, Time of Delivery:Jun., 1993. This Analyser have advanced functions on capture of electronic events and extra-high accurate measurement. Some features of the Analyser are follow: Band width 1 GHZ, sweeping speed 50ps/div, sampling rate 2G Sample per second, 8 bite accuracy wavefrom capture, 512_32768 points each time, and FFT function. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>TEK-CSA907A</B>, Error Bite Rate Test System, Time Delivery:Jun., 1993. The system composed by Pattern Generator(Tx),and Error Bite Rate Receiver(Rx). the system can be used flexible. Some features of the system are follow; Frequency Range 150kHz-700MHz, 16 bite program, 5 PRBS Pattern Output. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Hp-8702B Lightwave Component Analyser</B>,Time of Delivery:April, 1995. The Analyser is composed by Network Analyser, S-parameter test set, and E/O, O/E converter. the main features of the analyser for measurement of Transmission characteristic and Reflection Characteristic of optoelectronic devices and electronic devices are follow: Operating wavelength 0.85Um, 1.3Um. Frequency range 300kHz-6GHz. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>HP-8153a, Lightwave Multimeter</B>, Time of Delivery: Jan., 1995. There are two high stable 1.3umLaser diodes and two high stable optical power meter in the Multimeter. So we can combine them that the multimeter can measure parameters, such as loss, stability of optical fiber, fiber cable, fiber devices. It can be measured automatically. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>TEK-7104 Oscilloscope</B>, Time of Delivery: Jun., 1993. This is a high performance broadband analog oscilloscope. there are two 7A29 Amplifier Channel, two 7B15 Delaying Time Base, and several Probes. This oscilloscope can measure analog signal in frequency range DC to 1000MHz. Maximum input voltage &lt;10V rms on 50 input.)<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>TEK-VM700A Video Measurement Set,</B> Time of Delivery: April, 1995 The set is a advanced automatic measurement set. It can used as a Vector Oscilloscope, Noise measurement set, Nonlinear parameter, as well as other video parameter measurement set. The main features of the set are follow: high accuracy, high stale, and programming, and GD-IB, RS232 interface. A video signal generator is needed. <BR>
 <BR>
 <B>SUMI-35SE Fusion Splicer,</B> Time of Delivery: April, 1993. The splicer can automatically connect single mode fiber and multimode fiber with cladding diameter 80-150Um for S.M. and 0.02d for M.M. The main features of the splicer are follow: high automation, easy and fast operation. There are a set of compressible sleeves heater, for easy use.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>Hp-8593E Spectrum Analyzer</B>, Time of Delivery: April, 1995. This Analyser is from the HP Company. The HP-8593E spectrum analyzer is Small, lightweight, full function and automatic test instrument that cover the RF and microwave frequency ranges(9KHz-2.75GHz;2.75GHz-22GHz). Its minimum resolution is 30Hz. The instrument is mainly applied in spectrum analysis on Optical fiber communication system, of CATV system, of links, of delay lines and microwave system.<BR>
 <BR>
 <B>SPEX-1000M Spectrometer</B>, Time of Delivery: Jun., 1993. This instrument is from SPEX Industries, INC&gt;USA. SPEX-1000M spectrometer is composed of a one meter long main frame, a ministep driver(MSD2), signal processing system and computer interface, the controlling computer and its software. This instrument is mainly applied in the optical spectrum analysis on Lasers, Optical amplifiers, Nonlinear optics. Its optical wavelength range is 0-1500A; the resolution is 0.008nm; the accuracy is +- 0.05nm. <BR>
 
<HR>
<P><B>Since the establishment of the State Key Labs in Dec. 1990. Our main research directions are follow: Broadband lightwave transmission theory and technology; and boardband optical fiber transmission system and Networks. The research projects in four years are mainly in the area on optical fiber transmission theory and guidewave deceives, optical fiber CATV system, WDM devices, optical fiber amplifier, B-ISDN key technologies, and ATM networks. During four years, we completed 51 research projects, the total amount is about 6 million yuan. Among them, we were awarded more than 9 terms of national, provincial and ministry prizes. we have published totally 167 pap</B><B>ers and 7 books. </B><BR>
 <BR>
 <STRONG>The Laboratory attempt by many means to let its research projects approach the frontiers of national economic development demands in the area on ATM networks, HFC, as well as lightwave transmission system and related theory and devices. So that, we will accept the scientists, experts home and abroad are welcome to join us the research activities that we mentioned above. Our plan to accept scientists, experts is following: ATM Networks: 5; HFC: 5; System and Devices: 2. </STRONG>
<HR>
<P>Address: <BR>
State Key Lab of Broadband Fiber Transmission and Communication Networks, University of Electronic Science and Technology of China,<BR>
 Chengdu,Sichuan<BR>
 P.R.China <BR>
 610054<BR>
 
<UL>
<LI>Tel:(86)-28-3202261<BR>
 
<LI>Fax:(86)-28-3334131<BR>
 
</UL>
<P>
