<TITLE>Director of Lab </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>STATE KEY LABORATORY OF FUNCTIONAL POLYMER MATERIALS FOR ADSORPTION AND SEPARATION </H2>
<HR>
<P>
<H2>Director of Lab</H2>
<HR>
<H3></H3>
<H3>Huang Wenqiang</H3>
<P>Professor,   received his B. Sc.  degree in 1966,   his Ms.  degree in 1981 in the
 field of polymer  chemistry from Nankai University.  from 1967 to 1974  he 
worked in the Department of Chemistry,   Nankai University as Assistant.  Then 
he joined Yueyang General Petroleum Chemical Works,   Hunan Province as 
Assistant Engineer for 4 years.  Following his M. Sc.  degree,   he worked at 
the Department of Chemistry as Assistant in 1981.  Two years later he 
engaged in the research on the polymeric reagents as a visiting scientist 
at McGill University,   Canada from 1983 to 1985.  After he back to China,   he 
has worked in the Institute of Polymer Chemistry of Nankai University.  His 
professional career as a polymer chemist has included work in the research 
of synthesis and application of reactive functional polymer materials,  
including polymer reagents,   polymer catalysts,   polymer materials for 
separation through ion exchange and adsorption.<hr> 

<P><B>Phone:</B> 022-3502749 
<HR>
<P><B><ADDRESS>Email:</B> <A HREF="mailto:sorp@linux.nankan.edu.cn ">
 sorp@linux.nankan.edu.cn </A></ADDRESS>
</BODY>
