<HTML>
  <HEAD>
       <TITLE>Main Research Fields
       </TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY>
	<H2>
	STATE KEY LABORATORY OF RARE EARTH MATERIALS CHEMISTRY AND APPLICATIONS</H2><P>
	
        
	<PRE><H2>Main Research Fields</H2></PRE><P>
              
<HR>

<PRE>
	The main research of this laborotory id focused on rare earth chemistry 
and materials. Four research branches below are emphasized.

	1) Separation chemistry of rare earths. Research is focused on the new 
	   methodes, techniques, and theories of rare earth separation.

	2) Solid state chemistry of rare earths and materials. Research is focused
           on the X-ray luminescent and high-performance light-excited luminescent 
           materials, and the synthesis, properties and applications of composition 
           oxides of rare earth-transition metal.

	3) Coordination chemistry of rare earths. Research are focused on the 
        synthesis, structures, spectra and applications of rare earth compounds,
 	and the roles of rare earth complexes in medicine.

	4) Physical chemistry of rare earths and lanthanide theory. Research are 
	focused on the physical and chemical properties of rare earth complexes, 
	and the studies in electronic structures and chemical bonds of rare earths.

	The main target of the Lab. is to synthesis and develop novel rare earth 
compounds and materials.

</PRE>

  </BODY>
</HTML>
