2. Fluid Mechanics<BR>
3. Experimental Mechanics<BR>
4. Manufacturing Engineering<BR>
5. Welding<BR>
6. Mechanology<BR>
7. Optical Instruments Engineering<BR>
8. Measuring, Testing Techniques and Instruments<BR>
9. Precision Instruments &amp; Mechanics<BR>
10. Engineering Thermophysics<BR>
11. Internal Combustion Engines<BR>
12. Electrical Power Systems and their Automation<BR>
13. Signal and Information Processing<BR>
14. Architectural Design<BR>
15. Structure Engineering<BR>
16. Coastal Engineering<BR>
17. Inorganic Non-metallic materials<BR>
18. Chemical Engineering<BR>
19. Industrial Catalysis<BR>
20. Organic Chemical Technology<BR>
21. Applied Chemistry<BR>
22. Systems Engineering<BR>

<HR>
<H3>Note: The above mentioned 22 PH.D. specialities can also accept Master's degree students, General advanced students and Senior advanced students. </H3>
