<Title>Admission Qualifications for Candidates for a Master's degree</Title>
<h3>The applicant, who has a Bachelor's degree or holds the equivalent of 
Bachelor's degree in China, should submit his/her diploma, transcripts and 
recommendation letters from two professors or associate professors of his/her
major. He/She should be in good health and well behaved. Approved by the school, he/
she can apply for admission of Master's program at Tianjin University.
Acceptance is decided by selection after a screening process. The lectures 
will be given in English  or in Chinese.<P>
   If the application is a graduate from a Chinese university and wishes to study for
 a Master's degree at Tianjin University,he/she may be directly admitted with the
 recommendation and grades from his/her previous school along with knowledge of his/
her working capabilities.
</DOC>
