<Title>  Period of Schooling, Completion of Studies and the Awarding Degrees </Title>
<h2>1.Undergraduates:</h2>
<h3>
<UL>Usually lasts 4 years, a few courses require 5 years.<BR>
Certificates of graduation and academic degrees.</UL><HR></h3>
<h2>2. Candidates for a Master's degree:</h2> 
<h3><UL>
Lasts 2 to 3 years.<BR>
Certificates of graduation and Master's degrees</UL></h3><HR>
<h2>3. Candidates for a Doctorate:</h2>
<h3><UL>
Lasts 3 years.<BR>
Doctor's degree.<BR>
Those who have not completed the required courses and can not 
get degrees will receive certificates of advanced study.</UL></h3><HR>
<h2>4. Pre-studying Chinese Language Program:</h2> 
<h3><UL>
Lasts one years.<BR>
Certificates of completion of studies.</UL></h3><HR>
<h2>5. Long/Short Term Chinese Language Program:</h2> 
<h3><UL>
There is no specific time for schooling.<BR>
Certificates of completion of studies.</UL></h3><HR>
<h2>6. General Advanced Students:</h2> 
<h3><UL>
Lasts 1 to 2 years.<BR>
Certificates of advanced study</UL></h3><HR>
<h2>7. Senior Advanced Students:</h2> 
<h3><UL>
Lasts 1 to 2 years.<BR>
Certificates of advanced study</UL></h3><HR>
</DOC>
