<HEAD>

<TITLE>Syllabus '97 Workshops</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Wednesday, November 27, 1996  11:03 AM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BODY>



| <A HREF="syll97_cvr.htm">Workshop Agenda</A> | <A HREF="syll97_des.htm">Workshop Descriptions</A> | <A HREF="syll97_fac.htm">Workshop Faculty</A> |<br>
| <A HREF="syll97_lodg.htm">Fees, Lodging and Transportation</A> | <A HREF="syll97_reg.htm">Registration Form</A> | 
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5>Syllabus Workshops '97</FONT></CENTER>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER>Technology workshops for faculty</CENTER>
<CENTER>and </CENTER>
<CENTER>administrators</FONT><br>
<P>
<B>1997 Winter/Spring Schedule</B> </CENTER>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/syll97wkspcvr.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=0 ALIGN=TOP></CENTER>
<BR CLEAR = ALL>




<FONT color=red SIZE=3><CENTER>Intensive, full-day, hands-on workshops covering<br> critical academic technologies</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=3>Full-day workshops lead by experts<br>
on key education technologies</CENTER> </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=3>Hands-on sessions covering multimedia and<br> the World Wide Web in education</CENTER> </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=3>Workshops offered in both Macintosh<br>
and Windows platforms</CENTER> </FONT>
<p>
<br>
<FONT SIZE=5>Choose from the following full-day workshops:</FONT>
<P>
<B>Hands-On Workshops</B>
<HR WIDTH=50% SIZE=1 ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT color=red SIZE=3>Multimedia</FONT><br>
<li>Presentations and Multimedia in the Classroom
<li> Introduction to Multimedia Tools	
<li> Multimedia Authoring
<P>
<FONT color=red SIZE=3>The World Wide Web </FONT><br>
<li> The World Wide Web in Education
<li> Developing Courses for the World Wide Web
<li> Managing Courses on the World Wide Web
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER>Register now and save</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
Throughout the academic year, Syllabus Workshops '97 will present workshops in various locations convenient to college and university communities. Intensive, hands-on workshops will expand educators' knowledge and skill development in such important academic technologies as multimedia, the Internet, and the World Wide Web.
<P>
The schedule below reflects the Syllabus Workshops for the Northern California region for Winter/Spring '97. Additional workshop schedules will be announced throughout the year.
<P>
<FONT color=red SIZE=3>Who should attend?</FONT><br>
<HR WIDTH=50% SIZE=1 ALIGN=LEFT>
Syllabus Workshops are designed for college-level faculty and department chairs, college administrators, high school teachers, and education technology professionals who want to acquire in-depth skills and knowledge of the latest technologies for education. Both beginners and more advanced practitioners will benefit from these workshops.
<P>
<FONT color=red SIZE=3>Academic and continuing credit</FONT>
<HR WIDTH=50% SIZE=1 ALIGN=LEFT>
Earn 1 academic unit @ $35 or 1.5 continuing education units (CEUs) @ $30 for your participation in two days of workshops or seminars. Indicate your interest on the registration form.
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
