<HEAD>

<TITLE>classifieds</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Tuesday, December 17, 1996  3:58 PM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/classad.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=middle></CENTER>
<P>
<P ALIGN = CENTER><FONT SIZE=5>Syllabus Classifieds</FONT></P>
<p>
<B>How to Place Ads</B>
<P>
Ads may be submitted via, phone, fax, mail, or e-mail. You may use the attached form to submit ads and materials.
<P>
<B>E-mail:</B> Send to <A HREF="mailto:careers@syllabus.com">careers@syllabus.com</A> 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. <BR>
<B>Fax:</B> Send to 516-295-2675 EST,  or 408-746-2711 PST, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.  <BR>
<B>Phone:</B> Call 800-SYLLABUS (795-5228) and ask for Frank Buck (East coast) or Joann Scherrer (West coast)
<P>
<B>Surface:</B>  	
<P>
Syllabus Magazine<BR>
Classified ads<BR>
1307 S. Mary Avenue Suite 211<BR>
Sunnyvale, CA 94087		
<P>
<B>Ad Specifications</B>
<P>
<B>"By the word", or agate type classified listings:</B> Copy will appear in a single paragraph with no bold or italics. The first word will be bold denoting the subject area or discipline arranged in alphabetical order. Graphics can be included: see pricing information below.
<P>
<B>Display Ads:</B> We will accept camera-ready art, or text copy.  There is no charge for layout of ads that are 3" x 3" or larger and only require simple layout using the Syllabus magazine ad sizes. See recommended ad sizes on the next page. 
<P>
<B>Electronic art:</B> All graphics must be submitted separately. Graphics sent electronically must have been saved on either Mac or PC as a TIFF, PICT, EPS, or BMP at 300 dpi or greater. Graphics sent in by mail to convert to electronic data(scan) must be in the final desired size or larger and be sharp in clarity and resolution. Faxes and photocopies are acceptable for text submissions only and are not suitable as graphic material for reproduction.
<P>
<B>Materials:</B> Camera ready ads must be submitted in the following formats:<br>
120 to 133-line screen, right reading, emulsion down negatives are preferred for all display advertisements. Acceptable conversion materials include positives, i.e. a velox @ 100%, or laser print at 600 dpi or higher. Halftones screens should be 80 to 120 lines per inch (lpi). The publisher may use prior ad material if new material is not received by closing date.
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=1 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<A HREF="classindex.htm">back</A>


</BODY>
