<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>


<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=5>Sunday, March 9</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa1">MM1-Presentations and Multimedia in the Classroom (BEG)</A></B><BR>
Workshop leader: <B>Louis Molina</B>, Miami-Dade Community College<BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.)
<P>
<LI> <B>MM3-Multimedia Authoring/Macintosh</B><BR>
Workshop leader: <B>Diana Bajzek</B>, Carnegie Mellon University
A hands-on workshop for those who have some familiarity with multimedia technology (builds on the skills learned in Saturday's session on multimedia tools) Primary focus is on structuring multimedia data, designing end-user navigational controls, and providing interactivity using Lingo scripts. Participants work toward completion of a hands-on project in class. Applications used include: Macromedia Director and Extreme 3D. Other topics include the use of 3D modeling applications. 
<P>
<LI> <B>MM3-Multimedia Authoring/Windows</B><BR>
Workshop leader: <B>Tom Hall</B>, Pitt Community College
This workshop shows how the Windows authoring software, Multimedia ToolBook, can be used to create a variety of interactive multimedia applications. Participants learn some of the basics of ToolBook, including how to add multimedia components such as images, animation, and digital video. Learn how to use the Book Specialist to build a Generic Content book and a Generic Quiz book. Use the widgets found in the CBT Edition to quickly build an interactive quiz that provides scoring and feedback. 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa4">WEB1-The World Wide Web in Education (BEG)</A></B><BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.) 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa5">WEB2-Developing Courses for the World Wide Web</A></B><BR>
Workshop leader:<B>Robert Cavalier</B>, Carnegie Mellon University<BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.)  
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa5">WEB2-Developing Courses for the World Wide Web</A></B><BR>
Workshop leader: <B>Richard Knee</B>, Florida Atlantic University<BR>
(Repeated from above.) 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa7">WEB3-Managing Courses on the World Wide Web</A></B><BR>
Workshop leader: <B>Alistair Fraser</B>, Penn State University<BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.) 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa8">S1-Seminar: Issues in Distance Learning</A></B><BR>
Presenter: <B>Judith Boettcher</B>, Florida State University<BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.) 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa9">S2-Seminar: Institutional Support for Technology Programs</A></B> <BR>
(Please see description for Saturday's course.) 
<P>
<LI> <B><A HREF="miami97_sat.htm#sa10">S3-Seminar: Evaluating Effectiveness in Instructional 
