<TITLE>Miami Workshop '97</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Monday, February 10, 1997  11:32 PM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#B9B9DB">
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

| <A HREF="miami97_cvr.htm">Workshop Agenda</A> | <A HREF="miami97_fri.htm">Friday</A> | <A HREF="miami97_sat.htm">Saturday</A> | <A HREF="miami97_sun.htm">Sunday</A> |<br>
| <A HREF="miami97_lodg.htm">Fees, Lodging and Transportation</A> | <A HREF="miami97_reg.htm">Registration Form</A> | 

<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=5>Location, Lodging, and Transportation</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/miami97_02.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT SIZE=5>Location</FONT><BR>
From state route 595, exit at "Davie Road Extension"; look for signs "Colleges and Universities" and bear left (to the right if coming from the west). Travel on Davie Road and make a right turn at the 3rd light, Nova Drive. At the next intersection, College Ave., turn left. The entrance to Broward Community College's Library building and Florida Atlantic University's Liberal Arts building is the first left off of College Ave. Ample parking available.
<BR>
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<BR>
<FONT color=red SIZE=3>The conference site is less than a 10-minute drive from Ft. Lauderdale International Airport and approximately 45 minutes from Miami International Airport.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Lodging</FONT>
Rolling Hills Hotel and Golf Resort: The official resort of the NFL's Miami Dolphins, Rolling Hills has a reputation for providing excellent service. Located just a few miles west of Fort Lauderdale International Airport, the resort is within minutes of local centers of commerce, sightseeing attractions, and the area's famous beaches and a 5-minute drive from the Syllabus workshops. We have reserved a block of rooms for workshop participants at a special conference rate of $90 per night, single or double occupancy. <B>To reserve a room, call 1-800-327-7735 and be sure to mention Syllabus to obtain the discount rate. Reservations should be made before February 7, 1997.</B>
<P>
Fort Lauderdale Chamber of Commerce: Call 954-462-0600 for information on local area attractions.
<P>
<CENTER><FONT color=red SIZE=5>Fees and Discounts</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Transportation</FONT><BR>
Airlines: United Airlines is the official airline of Syllabus conferences and workshops. We have arranged discounts of 5% off any United or United Express published fare in effect when tickets are purchased. United and United Express unrestricted coach and first-class ticket purchasers will receive a 10% discount. To purchase discount tickets, call your travel agent or 1-800-521-4041, and reference the Syllabus97 conference code 511NN.
<P>
<B>Rental Car</B>: Hertz is offering rates from $23.99 per day and from $129.99 per week for Syllabus attendees, good from one week before the workshops to one week after. For a discount with Hertz, call 1-800-654-2240 and reference CV#18073.
<P>
<B>Airport Ground Transportation</B>: Courtesy shuttles are provided by Rolling Hills. At the baggage claim, use the courtesy phones to call 954-475-0400 x506 to arrange for a shuttle pick-up.
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Fees</FONT><BR>
All fees include admission to the Friday session and opening reception.<BR>
<P>
<TABLE WIDTH=50% BORDER=1 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>

  <TR>

    <TD>1 full-day workshop/seminar:</TD>    <TD>$250</TD>

  </TR>

  <TR>

    <TD>2 full-day workshops/seminars:</TD>    <TD>$425</TD>

  </TR>

</TABLE>

<P>
Full-day workshops or seminars run from 9:00AM-4:00PM and include lunch, coffee breaks, and materials.
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Discounts</FONT>
<P>
<B>Early registration:</B><BR>
<LI> Register by February 7, 1997, and receive a 10% discount.<BR>
<LI> Group registration discounts from a single institution (must be submitted as a group to qualify):<BR>
1-2 participants-no discount, 3-5 participants-5 percent discount, 6 or more participants-10 percent discount
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>How to contact Syllabus Workshops for registration </FONT>
<P>
<FONT color=red  SIZE=3>Call us at 1-800-773-0670 (within the U.S.), or (408) 746-2000 (outside the U.S.); fax (408) 746-2711, e-mail 
workshop@syllabus.com, visit our WWW site at http://www.syllabus.com, or wtite Syllabus Press, 1307 South Mary Ave., Suite 211, Sunnyvale, CA 94087 USA. Registrations are accepted by mail, phone, fax, e-mail, or via WWW.</FONT>
