<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER>Reader Service Highlights</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="jan97_BG.html"><FONT SIZE=5>January '97 Buyer's Guide</FONT></A></CENTER>
<P>
Below is a listing of some of the major companies offering products for the higher education market. Syllabus Reader Service allows you to obtain more information FREE from these companies You'll receive detailed product information, including demo disks or other samples where applicable.
<P>
<BR>
<B>Adobe Systems Inc.</B> provides the education community a variety of ways to create, communicate, and display information. From Adobe Acrobat to Adobe PageMill, universities can develop a total electronic publishing solution from Adobe's line of products.<br>
<INPUT NAME="rs1" VALUE="1" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #1<br> 
<P>
<B>Apollo Presentation Products</B> is a worldwide manufacturer and distributor of a complete line of products for every presentation need, from overhead projector, LCD panels, and slide and data/video projectors, to screens, easels, lamps, laminating equipment, laser pointers, and AV furniture. Recent introductions include upgraded versions of Apollo's Explorer multimedia projector and Vision Q series of LCD Panels, and four new LCD multimedia projectors: the Synergy, Passport, Express, and Escort.<br> 
<INPUT NAME="rs2" VALUE="2" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #2<br>
<P>
<B>Asymetrix Corp.</B>, located in Bellevue, Wash., is a leading supplier of easy-to-use Internet authoring and development tools for distributed learning, Web publishing, Internet application, and database development. Asymetrix products include ToolBook II, SuperCede, 3DF/X, Web 3D, InfoAssistant, and InfoModeler.<br>
<INPUT NAME="rs3" VALUE="3" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #3<br>
<P>
<B>Chisholm</B> has designed numerous LCD projectors, panels, and electronic writing products, which are sold through a worldwide network of audio-visual dealers. Chisholm's line of LCD projection products include the Aurora series of projectors and the Rainbow and DataBook series of active-matrix color LCD panels.<br>
<INPUT NAME="rs4" VALUE="4" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #4<br>
<P>
<B>Corel Systems</B> Corp.'s rapidly expanding product line encompasses a broad range of software-including graphics programs for every skill level, including business and publishing applications, a series of Internet tools, a desktop video conferencing solution, and a selection of multimedia titles for home or small office use. <br>
<INPUT NAME="rs5" VALUE="5" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #5<br>
<P>
<B>DAVIS North America</B> produces video presentation products. The company recently introduced a new line of DLP data and video projectors that offer high brightness with unique features for instructors' presentation needs. Small and compact, the DLP projectors, provide power zoom for easy positioning, icon-based menu for true plug and play setup, and presentation utility software for added impact. <br>
<INPUT NAME="rs6" VALUE="6" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #6<br>
<P>
<B>Dukane Corp.</B> offers audio visual products that deliver computer generated graphics and video. The ImagePro series of LCD data/video projectors are all-in-one projection devices that integrate a high-resolution color LCD panel with built-in light source.  All three OHP product groups feature superior optics, transmissive design and rack and pinion focus. Two of Dukane's latest releases include the ImagePro 7010 and the 5500 overhead projector. <br>
<INPUT NAME="rs7" VALUE="7" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #7<br>
<P>
<B>Elmo Mfg. Corp.</B> produces visual presenters, overhead projectors, 35mm slide projectors, and CCTV equipment. Elmo offers different models for every application including video conferencing and computer image capture. Two of the latest products are the DT-50 and the DT-100AF. These two products are desktop color document cameras that can be used for video conferencing.<br>
<INPUT NAME="rs8" VALUE="8" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #8<br>
<P>
<B>Hitachi Ltd.</B>, headquartered in Tokyo, Japan, is a  leading global electronics company that markets and manufactures a wide range of products, including computers, semiconductors, consumer products and power and industrial equipment. <br>
<INPUT NAME="rs9" VALUE="9" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #9<br>
<P>
<B>Proxima</B> recently announced a new video presentation bundle that will help enhance classroom instruction. The offer includes a Proxima multimedia projector (Lightbook LB10 notebook projector or Desktop Projectors models DP4100Z, DP4200Z, DP5500); the Tegrity Digital  Flipchart system including image capture and meeting management software, a video camera, and capture card; and an optional "visualizer" camera to project and capture paper documents.<br>
<INPUT NAME="rs11" VALUE="11" TYPE=CHECKBOX>Reader Service #11<br>
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
