<head>

<title>Carleton College, Northfield, Minnesota</title>

<!-- Date: 2/8/97 -->

</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC="images/classad.gif"ALT="graphic" VSPACE=0 HSPACE=0 ALIGN=middle>
<P>
<font size=5>Syllabus Classifieds</font>
<P>
<FONT color= red SIZE=3> <p ALIGN = RIGHT> posted 2/10/97</P></FONT>
<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>

<B>Position</B>: Computing Coordinator for the Languages & Literatures<BR>
<B>Institution</B>: Carleton College<BR>
<B>Location</B>: Minnesota<BR>
<P>
<B>Note</B>: 
<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<B>Carleton College</B><br>
<B>Northfield, Minnesota</B>
<P>
COMPUTING COORDINATOR FOR THE LANGUAGES & LITERATURES
<P>
Carleton College invites individuals with a strong background in modern
languages and literatures, excellent computing skills, a keen desire to
enhance teaching through the application of information technologies, and
an enthusiasm for working with people, to apply for the full time position
of Computing Coordinator for the Languages and Literatures. Individuals who
have completed significant graduate work in a foreign language/literature
program are particularly invited to apply.
<P>
The Coordinator will work closely with faculty, staying current with
individual teaching and research practices and needs; aggressively pursue
knowledge of information technology applications in the Languages and
Literature; translate technologies into locally useful instructional and
scholarly tools; provide individual assistance including technology
exploration, consultation, troubleshooting, and training.
<P>
Qualifications: Bachelor's degree or higher; degree or emphasis in at least
one foreign language and/or literature program. Minimum two years
post-college end-user support experience. Experience and understanding of
teaching and research in the Languages and Literatures. Solid experience
and understanding of DOS/Windows, Windows 95,  and/or Macintosh, VMS or
UNIX; NetWare and/or AppleShare; the TCP/IP Internet. Substantial
experience with foreign language word processing, Web authoring, OCR,
computer-assisted language instruction, and multimedia authoring. Excellent
oral and written communication skills. Strong service orientation.
<P>
Carleton College is a highly selective, coeducational, residential,
non-sectarian liberal arts college with 1,850 studens and approximately 200
faculty. The college is located 45 miles south of the twin cities of
Minneapolis and St. Paul. Academic Computing and Networking Services was
created in 1993 to support campus-wide curricular enhancement through the
use of information technologies. A full description of this position may be
found at <A HREF="http://www.carleton.edu/campus/ACNS/">http://www.carleton.edu/campus/ACNS/.</A>
<P>
Salary commensurate with qualifications and experience. Benefits package
applies. To apply, submit a resume and contact information for three
references to  Cathy Smith, Director, Academic Computing & Networking
Services, Carleton College, One North College Street, Northfield, MN 55057;
cathy.smith@carleton.edu. Applications will be reviewed starting February
21, 1997 and continue until an appoitment is made. AA/EOE.
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=1 ALIGN=LEFT>
