<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>

<B>Position</B>: Dean of Undergraduate Studies<BR>
<B>Institution</B>: Chaminade University of Honolulu<BR>
<B>Location</B>: Honolulu, Hawaii<BR>
<P>
<B>Note</B>: 
<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>

<B>Chaminade University of Honolulu</B>
<P>
Dean of Undergraduate Studies: Chaminade University of Honolulu is seeking
a Dean of Undergraduate Studies to provide leadership in the development of
academic programs and the enhancement of academic life generally. Chaminade
University is a Roman Catholic university, founded by the Society of Mary
(Marianists), committed to quality professional programs and the personal
development of its students. The university has 2,500 students, traditional
and non-traditional enrolled in 21 majors.
<P>
The Dean of Undergraduate Studies will offer leadership for the faculty in
the development of a strong academic program related to the university's
mission and give assistance to the Vice President for Academic plans,
policies, and procedures. The Dean will support the continuous enhancement
of teaching, research, advising, and service and he/she will lead in the
creation and implementation of effective systems of programatic and
curricula assessment.
<P>
Requirement: Ph.D or other terminal degree; a record of distinguished
teaching and scholarly achievement which would justify appointment at full
professor level; at least two years of administrative experience in a
college or university; excellent organizational, communictions, personal
commitment to the mission and goals of Chaminade University.
Salary is competitive. Those interested should send application letter,
curriculum vitae, transcripts from institution awarding highest degree, and
the names and telephone numbers of at least five references. Send
application to: Dr. Rodney Kilcup, Vice President for Academic and Student
Affairs, Chaminade University, 3140 Waialae Avenue, Honolulu, HI
96816-1578. Chaminade University is an Equal Opportunity Affirmative Action
Employer.
<P>
