<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>

<B>Position</B>: Manager, Instructional Technology Services<br>
<B>Institution</B>: Princeton University<br>
<B>Location</B>: New Jersey<br>
<P>
<B>note</B>: 
<HR WIDTH=100% noshade SIZE=3 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>
<B>Princeton University</B>
<P>
Manager, Instructional Technology Services: The Office of Computing and Information Technology (CIT) at Princeton University seeks a manager for Instructional Technology Services (ITS). The Manager is responsible for facilities and staff with a mission to support integration of instructional computing technologies across the curriculum of the University. ITS facilities include: the PLACE, Princeton's New Media Center; and the Language Laboratory, which houses the university's video library. Under the active and hands-on leadership of this manager, ITS staff members develop programs, services, and innovative projects that support teaching and learning. The ITS manager collaborates with other CIT managers and campus colleagues in the library and the academic departments to develop and implement new instructional projects and delivery services. The manager participates in long-range planning and project implementation with colleagues in CIT's Instructional and Media Services group. The ITS manager will report to the Manager for Instructional and Media Services within CIT's Information Services Directorate.
<P>
Qualifications: Bachelor's degree in a discipline taught at Princeton preferred; an advanced degree-preferably in instructional technology or design-or equivalent experience is required. Minimum of five years providing instructional technology support directly to faculty members is essential, as is substantial prior experience managing instructional support teams or groups. Classroom teaching experience desirable. Necessary technical skills include: thorough knowledge of PC/Mac hardware, software, and multimedia applications; extensive experience with Web-based development tools; familiarity with strategies for network delivery of applications and materials. Programming experience or knowledge of database design is desirable.
<P>
Applicants should send a resume and a letter of application including two references to: Bruce Finnie, Computing & Information Technology, 87 Prospect Ave., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08544. E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:finnie@Princeton.edu">finnie@Princeton.edu</A>. Phone: (609) 258-3068. Fax: (609) 258-3943.
