<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Syllabus '96 Exhibitors</TITLE><!-- Date: Tuesday, June 11, 1996  7:33 PM --></HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="images/sconf_bkground.gif"><FONT SIZE=5><CENTER>Syllabus '96</CENTER></FONT><CENTER><FONT SIZE=5>Exhibitors and Corporate Presenters</FONT></CENTER><CENTER>(A complete listing will be made available in late June)</CENTER><P><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Adobe Systems Inc.</FONT> creates software that makes computer-based design as limitless as the human mind. It has continued to grow, adapt, and innovate to meet head-on, the challenges and opportunities that are taking computer publishing to regions beyond the desktop, and beyond even paper itself. Adobe occupies a special place in the ever-expanding information landscape. No other software has the breadth and depth of experience to deliver a total solution that lets people communicate in the most expressive and effective way over any medium, from paper to compact disc, from servers to the Internet. Adobe develops software standards that enable visually rich information to flow freely. For more information, access <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com">www.adobe.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Adobe Systems Inc.<BR> 1585 Charleston Rd.<BR>Mountain View, CA 94039<BR>(800) 833-6687<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Academic Systems</FONT> is a leading developer of multimedia learning systems for higher education. The company's mission is to work in partnership with colleges and universities to enable faculty to improve student academic achievement. Currently, Academic Systems offers three courses in mathematics and is developing additional courses in English, math, and other areas. These courses are based on a new instructional model called Mediated Learning -- a faculty-guided, learner-centered method of instruction that takes advantage of the combined strengths of instructors, students, and multimedia technology to create an individualized learning environment and increase student academic success. Located in Mountain View, California, Academic Systems was founded in 1992 by Dr. Bernard R. Gifford, Ph.D., former dean of the Graduate School of Education at the University of California, Berkeley, and former vice president of education for Apple Computer. The AcademicNet Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.academic.com"> www.academic.com</a><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>Academic Systems <br>444 Castro St., Ste. 1200<br>Mountain View, CA 94041<br>(415) 694-6850<br><p><br><FONT SIZE=5>A.D.A.M. Software Inc.</FONT> creates, publishes, and markets multimedia software based on human anatomy. A.D.A.M. (Animated Dissection of Anatomy for Medicine) is a multimedia system for Windows and Macintosh computers, which promotes interactive learning via a comprehensive simulation of human anatomy. A.D.A.M. Scholar Series products illustrate complex anatomical interrelationships and enable students to conceptualize and internalize difficult subject matter. The A.D.A.M. Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.adam.com"> www.adam.com</a><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>A.D.A.M. Software Inc.<br>1899 Powers Ferry Rd., Ste. 460<br>Marietta, GA 30067<br>(800) 755-ADAM<br><p><br><FONT SIZE=5>Allegiant Technologies Inc.</FONT>, develops and markets innovative multimedia, Internet, and application development software that empowers people to interactively communicate, educate, entertain, and manage information. Allegiant will feature its latest version of SuperCard, the cross-platform authoring tool for building interactive, multimedia applications. SuperCard is ideal for creating computer-based training and education reference projects, author personal applications and CD-ROM titles, develop multimedia brochures, and more. Allegiant will also feature Marionet, a script-level interface to the Internet that gives developers and power users the capability to build custom Internet solutions using popular authoring or productivity applications. The Allegiant home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.allegiant.com">www.allegiant.com</A>. <BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Allegiant Technologies Inc.<BR>9740 Scranton Rd., Ste. 300<BR>San Diego, CA 92121<BR>(619) 587-0500<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Apple Computer Inc.'s</FONT> The idea of schools without boundaries is at the heart of Apple Computer vision for the 21st century-a world where electronic information enhances collaboration and communication throughout the learning community. As college and university administrators, faculty, and students prepare for the next century, Apple seeks to enhance their learning experience, opening new opportunities for instruction, teaching, research, and collaborative learning. Apple's vision for a learning society is to provide productivity tools for administrators, faculty, and students to analyze, understand, create, and present information and ideas "anywhere, anytime" based on an individual's needs, interests, and curiosities. The Apple Higher Education site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://hed.info.apple.com"> hed.info.apple.com</a><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>Apple Computer Inc.<br>1 Infinite Loop<br>Cupertino, CA 95014<br>(800) 538-9696<br><p><br><FONT SIZE=5>Asymetrix Corporation</FONT> is a leading supplier of easy-to-use Internet authoring and development tools for distributed learning, Web publishing, Internet application, and database development. Asymetrix products include ToolBook II, SuperCede, 3DF/X, Web 3D, InfoAssistant, and InfoModeler. Asymetrix will be demonstrating ToolBook II, the industry's most comprehensive solution for creating and deploying Internet-based distributed learning. For more information access <A HREF="http://www.asymetrix.com">www.asymetrix.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Asymetrix Corp.<BR>110-110th Ave., N.E., Ste. 700<BR>Bellevue, WA 98004<BR>(800) 448-6543<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Better Education Inc.</FONT> will demonstrate Classtalk, a fully interactive classroom communication system that networks calculators, laptops, or palmtops to a teachers desktop computer. Classtalk allows every student to participate in every question or problem presented during a class by an instructor. The instructor can then monitor who understands and who needs additional help. Classtalk can also be used for group activities, which includes a consensus with dissent (Supreme Court) model. <BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Better Education Inc.<BR>4824 George Washington Hwy., Ste. 103<BR>Yorktown, VA 23692<BR>(804) 898-4846<br><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>The California State University (CSU)</FONT> is the largest system of senior higher education in the country with 22 campuses, over 320,000 students and 10,000 full-time faculty members. Syllabus '96 visitors to the CSU booth will see four examples--in the areas of science, fine arts, business and social sciences--of how information technology resources have been leveraged to benefit all campuses in the system.  Cal Poly San Luis Obispo will demonstrate a Graphical User Interface to access and analyze information from large financial databases used in economics and business courses and talk about data and services available through the Business Database Specialty Center. CSU Hayward will showcase a DELTA Project supported system for operating a Scanning Electron Microscope located on the campus from remote sites using commonly available equipment andsoftware.  San Jose State University will demonstrate modules from The Web of Art, a course in the history of World Art and Culture that makes use of images digitized and catalogued as part of  CSU DELTA Project.  Finally, San Francisco State will demonstrate instructional applications of Geographic Information System software developed by ESRI and talk about services provided by the Geographic Information System Specialty Center.  For more information visit the following Web sites: <A HREF="http://www.calstate.edu">http://www.calstate.edu</A>; <A HREF="http://www.calpoly.edu">http://www.calpoly.edu</A>; <A HREF="http://www.hal.csuhayward.edu">http://www.hal.csuhayward.edu</A>; <A HREF="http://www.sjsu.edu">http://www.sjsu.edu</A>; <A HREF="http://www.sfsu.edu">http://www.sfsu.edu</A><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>The California State University System Office<br>400 Golden Shore<br>Long Beach, CA 90802<br>(310) 985-2500<br><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Casady & Greene Inc.</FONT> provides easy to use solutions for one's software needs.  Featuring our Eddy Award winning utility, Conflict Catcher 3, which was rated a "must have" by MacUser magazine and our new Simplified Office Solutions suite of products K.I.S.S. & Spell Catcher. K.I.S.S. (Keep It Simple Spreadsheet) shows numerical calculation in a clear and easy-to-understand format. Spell Catcher offers spell checking, thesaurus, and shorthand glossary globally in any application as well as the Internet. Other products include InfoGenie, Snap Mail 2.0, and a wide array of award-winning utility, font, and entertainment titles. The Casady and Greene Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://205.179.133.2/C&G/Welcome.html"> 205.179.133.2/C&G/Welcome.html</a><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Casady & Greene Inc.<BR>22734 Portola Dr.<BR>Salinas, CA 93908-1119<BR>(408) 484-9228<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Cel Educational Resources</FONT> is the producer of The Video Encyclopedia of the 20th Century, a 42-laserdisc, 83-hour archive of fully referenced primary source full-motion video, with accompanying software available for Macintosh and Windows platforms. CEL's new titles include Set On Freedom: The American Civil Rights Movement, a Level I/III interactive laserdisc tracing the movement from 1954 through 1968; and American Government, a Houghton Mifflin videodisc, which takes a one-hour look at Parties and Campaigns, Civil Rights and Equality, the Presidency and Watergate. <BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Cel Educational Resources<BR>60 E. 42nd. St.<BR>New York, NY 10165<BR>(212) 953-4650<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Charles River Media Inc.</FONT> publishes books and software for the educational training market and computing professionals. Our titles include The Internet WatchDog, which monitors and does not block Internet activity, HP-48G/GX Investigations in Mathematics, the HTML TemplateMASTER CD, which includes tutorials, clip art, and templates for creating Web pages, and the Internet Training CD. Early '96 titles will feature Netscape Navigator 2.0: A Jumpstart Tutorial, the World Wide Web Encyclopedia CD, the AOL Web Browser Handbook, and Creating Computer Art Using Dabbler. The Charles River Media home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.algorithm.com/crm">www.algorithm.com/crm</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Charles River Media Inc.<BR>P.O. Box 417, 403 VFW Dr.<BR>Rockland, MA 02370<BR>(617) 871-4184<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Chisholm</FONT> was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in the Silicon Valley. Chisholm has designed numerous LCD color projectors, panels, and electronic writing products, which are sold through a worldwide network of audio-visual dealers. Chisholm's line of LCD projection products include the Aurora series of projectors and the Rainbow and DataBook series of active-matrix color LCD panels. These multimedia products support the VGA and Macintosh computers as well as multiple video and audio sources. Many models feature 16.7 million colors, a built-in speaker, and Chisholm's exclusive electronic chalkboard that can annotate computer and video images.<BR> <P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Chisholm<BR>910 Campisi Way<BR>Campbell, CA 95008<BR>(800) 888-4210<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>COMPanion Corp.</FONT> offers Lancaster, a product that allows instructors to teach over the computer network, i.e. send and retrieve files such as tests, see student screens, broadcast their own or a student's screen to the whole class, create individual student Electronic Portfolios, and collect lab usage statistics-all from the teacher's computer. Teachers can now setup and shutdown lab computers, launch applications, lock computers, and more-with the click of a button. Lancaster saves the teachers' time and increases the students' time on tasks. Free 5-user trial version available. <p><B>Contact info:</B><br>COMPanion Corp.<br>1831 E. Fort Union Blvd.<br>Salt Lake City, UT 84121<br>(800) 347-6439<br><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Compression Labs Inc. (CLI)</FONT>, headquartered in San Jose, Calif., is a recognized leader in video communications. As the pioneer of compressed digital video technology, the company manufactures and markets the highest quality video conferencing products that enable people at different locations to see and interact with one another in a natural, intuitive manner. CLI supplies group and desktop video solutions to organizations-large and small-for a variety of applications including distance learning and remote-site training. In the U.S., customers in 44 of the 50 states use CLI video conferencing for education. Founded in 1976, CLI has sales offices across the U.S., with international offices in Australia, Belgium, Japan, and The People's Republic of China. For more information, access the CLI Web site at <A HREF="http://www.clix.com">www.clix.com</A><BR><p><B>Contact info:</B><BR>CLI Inc.<BR>350 E. Plumera Dr.<BR>San Jose, CA 95131-1911<BR>(800) 538-7542<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Corel Corp.</FONT> incorporated in 1985, is the second largest independent vendor of personal productivity applications worldwide. Corel's rapidly expanding product line encompasses a broad range of software-including graphics programs for every skill level, business and publishing applications, a series of Internet tools, a desktop video conferencing solution, and a wide selection of quality multimedia titles for home or small office use. The company's family of business applications, including the world renowned WordPerfect product line, delivers fully integrated software solutions that can be customized to suit any user's needs. Offering a growing collection of highly complementary products, Corel leads the industry in providing competitively priced, world-class software. The Corel home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.corel.com">www.corel.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Corel Corp.<BR>1600 Carling Ave.<BR>Ottawa Ontario Canada K1Z 8R7<BR>(613) 761-9176<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Creation Engine</FONT> strives to deliver the future to the academic community. Creation Engine is dedicated to providing prompt service, a working knowledge of multimedia tools, and low prices to the academic multimedia market.  Academic discount prices are available to accredited schools, faculty, and students. Creation Engine offers great academic discount prices on multimedia, graphics, and internet development tools from Adobe, Allegiant Tech, auto*des*sys, Autodesk, Caligari, Fractal Design, g/matter design, Hash, Macromedia, MetaTools, Microsoft, Specular, Strata, Wacom, and more. The Creation Engine Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.cengine.com">www.cengine.com</A><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Creation Engine<BR>2435 Whitney Dr.<BR>Mountain View, CA 94043<BR>(800) 431-8713<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>The Daedalus Group Inc.</FONT>, for nearly 10 years has been a leader in computer-based writing and language instruction and has produced the award-winning Daedalus Integrated Writing Environment (DIWE). This easy-to-use software combines a dozen tools to help students communicate more effectively, think critically, and learn collaboratively. The founders of Daedalus are teachers who recognize the challenges of integrating technology and education. We also support instructors through electronic discussion groups, newsletters, course material databases, updated Web resources, virtual classroom space, on-site consulting, regional training workshops, and free technical assistance. We have helped hundreds of classes across the curriculum and around the world transform computers into tools for dynamic learning. To learn how Daedalus can help you engage your students, access <A HREF="http://www.daedalus.com">www.daedalus.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact:</B><BR>Daedalus Group Inc.<BR>1106 Clayton Lane, #250W<BR>Austin, TX 78723<BR>(800) 879-2144<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>DeltaPoint Inc.</FONT> is the publisher of QuickSite, WebAnimator, and DeltaGraph software, and is committed to providing customers with streamlined, easy-to-use on-line and desktop visualization software solutions. QuickSite for Windows is designed to speed the creation of Web pages and streamline site management for end users through helpful Wizards, automatic HTML code generation, automatic page link creation, and database technology. WebAnimator for Macintosh is a set of tools that quickly creates and delivers multimedia animations over the Web. DeltaGraph is an advanced charting and graphing solution for Macintosh and Windows. QuickSite and WebAnimator will be cross platform in September. The DeltaPoint Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.deltapoint.com">www.deltapoint.com</A><br><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>DeltaPoint Inc.<br>22 Lower Ragsdale Dr.<br>Monterey, CA 93940<br>(408) 648-4000<br><P><br><FONT SIZE=5>Deneb Robotics Inc.</FONT>, founded in 1985 and privately held, is today a world leader in 3D graphics-based factory simulation, telerobotic, and virtual reality software. Its products are known for their patented user-friendly menus, comprehensive application functionality including built-in libraries and automatic processing of common operations, and an open architecture for applications involving remote control of automated devices interfacing with external databases or integration of multiple system components. Deneb Robotics' simulation and telerobotic software is widely used in the aerospace, automotive, defense, environmental, medical, nuclear, and research communities. With offices in Europe, Scandinavia, Japan, Korea, India, and the United States, Deneb Robotics has earned an international reputation for physics-based simulation products that combine ease of use with state-of-the-art "virtual environment" technologies and methodologies. The Deneb Robotics home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.deneb.com">www.deneb.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Deneb Robotics Inc.<BR>3285 Lapeer Road West<BR>P.O. Box 214687<BR>Auburn Hills, MI 48321-4687<BR>(810) 377-6900<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Dukane Corp.</FONT> offers a full line of presentation products, which are ideal for computer-based training, lectures, and classroom instruction. The ImagePro Series LCD Projector is PC-and Macintosh-compatible and has the capability to project both video and computer graphics. Dukane also manufactures a series of High-Intensity Overhead Projectors, which can be used for LCD projection panel presentations. Rated between 5500 and 8500 ANSI lumens, the High-Intensity series provides users with high light output and graphic clarity. The Dukane home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.industry.net/dukane.av">www.industry.net/dukane.av</A><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Dukane Corp.<BR>2900 Dukane Dr.<BR>St. Charles, IL 60174<BR>(800) 676-2486<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>DynEd International</FONT>, founded in 1988, develops listening-based interactive multimedia programs that create an optimal learning environment to teach English, Spanish, and Japanese to non-native speakers. DynEd courseware is created by experienced teachers and is based on instructional strategies and techniques developed over many years of successful teaching. Combining classroom proven teaching methods with state-of-the-art multimedia technology, DynEd programs demonstrate our commitment to "Dynamic Education." DynEd courseware gives students the intensive practice necessary to acquire new lan