.com">www.fractal.com</A><BR><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Fractal Design<BR>101-B Rancho Dr.<BR>San Jose, CA 95111<BR>(408) 363-9898<BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>The H.W. Wilson Company</FONT> provides information in the form of high-quality reference, educational, and professional materials. All of our Full Text, Abstracts, and Index Databases will be on display for demonstration. Wilson databases are available through WILSONDISC CD-ROM, WILSONTAPE Databases Licensing, WILSONLINE online, and through our information partners. Ask for a free copy of the latest WILSONDISC Sampler. The H.W. Wilson home page can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.hwwilson.com">www.hwwilson.com</A><P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>H.W. Wilson<BR>950 University Ave.<BR>Bronx, NY 10452 <BR>(800) 367-6770 <BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Inline Inc.</FONT> produces V-Net, an interactive learning system for CBT facilities compatible with PCs, Macintosh computers, and SUN Workstations operating at any video resolution. Featuring video sharing, remote keyboard and mouse control, intercom and optional stereo audio sharing for multimedia applications, V-Net enhances lectures, lab sessions, and collaborative learning projects. An instructor can view any students' workstation video signal, send a video signal to any or all students, blank student monitors to get their attention, or route any workstation signal to a large screen projector. Control can be established using a remote keyboard or mouse control. The system also permits flexible options for each student allowing them to request attention from any instructor, select the video source for their monitor, control intercom functions, and engage remote keyboard and mouse control for collaborative learning sessions.<P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Inline Inc.<BR>1901 E. Lambert Rd., Ste. 110 <BR>La Habra CA 90631 <BR>(800) 882-7117 <BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Instructional Performance Systems Inc. (IPSI)</FONT> was launched with a curriculum development software suite that had undergone two years of intensive development and use by technical colleges throughout Minnesota. This development was the result of cloning the Vogler Curriculum Pedagogy Assessment (CPA) model as manifested in Dr. Daniel E. Vogler's text, Performance Instruction: Planning, Delivering, Evaluating, and Analyzing. The text evolved from more than two decades of work with educational and training enterprises. The company has experienced success with more than 10,000 users in the education and the business sector. The original products have been upgraded and new products have been conceptualized and developed. Consultative services relate to training, implementation, and local policy analysis. <P><B>Contact info:</B><BR>Instructional Performance Systems Inc.<BR>938 Prairie Center Dr., Ste. 130 <BR>Eden Prairie, MN 55344 <BR>(612) 835-2262 <BR><P><BR><FONT SIZE=5>Iomega Corp.</FONT> provides personal computer storage solutions that help people manage their computer files. These solutions consist of Zip drives and disks; Jaz one-gigabyte drives and disks; Ditto tape backup drives and tape cartridges; and the Bernoulli line of removable drives and disks. Iomega also provides the academic community with support, services, and product bundles specifically tailored to that market with its IomegaSmart education initiative. Used in homes, business, government, and education, Iomega storage solutions are available through computer retail stores, resellers, and major distributors. The Iomega Web site can be accessed at <A HREF="http://www.iomega.com">www.iomega.com</A><p><B>Contact info:</B><br>Iomega Corp.<br>1821 W. Iomega Way<br>Roy, UT 84067<br>(800) 697-8833<br><p><br><FONT SIZE=5> International Thomson Publishing Higher Education </font> is comprised of Brooks/Cole, Heinle & Heinle, PWS, South-Western College, TCI Software Research, and Wadsworth publishing companies. Today we are bringing to you multimedia products developed s