<HTML><HEADER><TITLE>Classroom Products and Technology Infrastructure: A Buyer's Guide</TITLE></HEADER><body><center><h2><strong>Classroom Products and Technology Infrastructure:<br>A Buyer's Guide</strong></h2></center><hr>A guide to the products that support technology integration on campus.<hr><strong>Authoring Tools</strong><br><P><strong>Open!Info Manager</strong><br>Open!Info Manager multimedia construction kit is a Windows-based software package combining multimedia authoring and media management capabilities. It has a menu-driven graphical user interface and an object-oriented database that allows storage, retrieval, and previewing of audio, video, animation, graphics, and text. All media imported into the database can be previewed from within the Open!Info Manager program and incorporated into any presentation or multimedia project. In addition, the application automates the final publishing and distribution process by assembling all the elements such as media elements, runtime player software, and a final set-up program. $299. Contact: Horizons Technology Inc., San Diego, CA; (800) 828-3808. <p><strong>The Instructor</strong><br>The Instructor, by BCD Assoc., is a multimedia authoring system that runs under the Windows Object-Based Authoring interface. Designed to be easy to learn, The Instructor supports graphic file formats that include .FLI, FLC, .WAV, and AVI. It also comes with a royalty-free Runtime module that advertises the author's content and not itself, making it ideal for commerical title distribution. $795. Contact: BCD Assoc., Oklahoma City, OK; (405) 843-4576. <hr><strong>Projection Panels</strong><br><p><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/colortouch.GIF"><strong>ColorTouch</strong><br>The Crestron ColorTouch PCT-3000CLR is a 10-inch diagonal touchscreen control panel. ColorTouch utilizes VisionTools software, enabling users to create and manipulate combinations of graphics, buttons, and icons in a full range of color. ColorTouch works with systems that have display panels using electroluminescent (EL) or double supertwist (DST) technology. Contact: Crestron Electronics Inc., Cresskill, NJ; (800) 237-2041. <br clear=both><br><img hspace=10 align=right src="images/viewframe.GIF"><strong>VIEWFRAME TFT</strong><br>Developed for the education market, VIEWFRAME TFT is a projection panel that comes in a computer data-only model and a computer data plus full-motion video model. The compact device, which displays up to 1.4 million colors, has automatic source signal recognition that selects the appropriate setup parameters and needs minimal manual adjustment. The panel offers three input ports enabling instructors to have simultaneous connection to one computer and two video sources. Pricing starts at $2,495. Contact: nView Corp., Newport News, VA; (800) 736-8439.<br clear=both><hr><strong>Projectors</strong><br><p><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/PLC.GIF"><strong>PLC-500M</strong><br>The PLC-500M is a data and video LCD projector designed for portable presentations. It is capable of projecting an output of 550 lux that can evenly display an image on screen sizes up to 150 inches. The device also has input capabilities including composite video, S-Video, and V.G.A. inputs that are compatible with PC and Macintosh-based computers. Contact: Sanyo Industrial Video Division; (818) 998-7322.<br clear=both><br><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/Polaview.GIF"><strong>Polaview 105</strong><br>Polaroid Corp.s new Polaview line of LCD projectors range from the low-end Polaview 45 up to the Polaview 105. Each device functions as an overhead projector and LCD panel in a self-contained unit that can deliver presentations from a personal computer or portable notebook computer. Polaview 105 is a polysilicon projector that can produce images in up to 16.7 million colors. The motorized zoom lens with focus control can be operated by a remote control or from a keypad on the projector. Multiple computer and video inputs enable dual presentations and it can display images more than 30 feet in size diagonally. $9,495. Contact: Polaroid Corp., Cambridge, MA; (800) 816-2611. <p><strong>PC Cam</strong><br>Sony's new PC Cam is a combination miniature video camera and microphone designed for desktop applications ranging from videoconferencing to making still shots. Features include a 10-inch bendable arm, a rotating CCD (charged coupled device) camera head, and manual focus and iris control, which allows video capture under varying lighting conditions. $499. Contact: Sony Electronics, Park Ridge, NJ; (201) 930-6981. <p><strong>BarcoData 3100 LC</strong><br>BARCO Display Products recently released the BarcoData 3100 LC high-end LCD light-valve projector. Featuring a compact design, the projector is equipped with a built-in pixel map processor that maximizes light output and resolution by converting all incoming signals to the full resolution of the LCD panels. $27,495. Contact: The BARCO Group, Kennesaw, GA; (404) 590-7900. <p><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/VPH.GIF"><strong>VPH-1292Q</strong><br>Sony Electronics has a high-end graphics projection system that provides front and rear projection viewing capabilities. The system has a high-resolution nine-inch electromagnetic focus CRT and features horizontal scanning frequencies from 15-135 kHz, and vertical scanning frequencies from 38-150 Hz. Contact: Sony Electronics, Park Ridge, NJ; (201) 930-6981. <br clear=both><hr><strong>Video Conferencing Products</strong><br><p><strong>SMART 2000 Conferencing</strong><br>SMART Technologies produces SMART 2000 Conferencing software for Windows-based systems. The software enables groups of people in up to 64 locations to communicate over ordinary telephone lines or computer networks. Users can share information and images electronically as well as annotate and edit information in real time. $299. Contact: SMART Technologies Inc., Calgary, AB Canada; (403) 245-0333. <p><strong>ShowStation</strong><br>ShowStation is a document conferencing projector that allows users to review and make revisions in real time. The device can transmit images of transparencies, glossies, photographs, and small objects. When working in conjunction with SoundStation, teleconferencing participants can interactively view, annotate, and print documents or data files. $10,795. Contact: Polycom Inc., San Jose CA; (408) 526-9000. <p><strong>CameraMan</strong><br>ParkerVision Inc. is offering CameraMan, a camera that can be used for distance learning. Using Personal Locator Keypads, up to 99 students can attract the instructor's attention by pressing a button that instructs the camera to focus in on the student. CameraMan has the capability to support up to 30 press-to-talk or voice-activated microphones. $4,995. Contact: ParkerVision Inc., Jacksonville, FL 32256; (800) 532-8034. <p><strong>Model 2004 MCS</strong><br>VideoServer Inc., a supplier of standards-based Multimedia Conference Servers (MCS), released Model 2004 MCS, a new, low-priced addition to its product family of videoconferencing products. It supports up to eight conference endpoints and has the capability to run the same software as higher-end models of the MCS product line. Model 2004 has three hardware slots that can accept VideoServer BPU conference cards, network interface cards, or inverse multiplexor bandwidth management cards. Connectivity capabilities include support for Primary Rate ISDN, T1, Fractional T1, E1, Fractional E1, and Switched 56 T1 Access. Pricing starts at $25,000. VideoServer Inc., Lexington, MA; (617) 863-2300. <p><strong>TeleTrack</strong><br>Howard Enterprises Inc. offers three TeleCamera models for video communications. A new product called TeleTrack is a TeleCamera positioning device for videoconferencing. It can be mounted on the side of a computer monitor and allows the user to adjust the TeleCamera vertically, and it also provides a tilt and swivel adjustment. For document imaging, the camera can be tilted more than 90 degrees to view an object on a desktop. $59.95. Contact: Howard Enterprises Inc., Camarillo, CA; (805) 383-7444.<hr><strong>Multimedia Presentation Devices and Peripherals</strong><br><p><strong>CAPS-II</strong><br>CAPS-II is a hardware and software combination for creating and incorporating multimedia presentations into classrooms. The hardware, produced by PRC Inc., consists of a Power Macintosh, audio and video output, Apple CD, FlexCam video camera, networking capability, a cabinet that encloses all of the hardware, and many optional features including scanners and printers. A communications panel also provides access to the Internet and video conferencing. The software included with CAPS-II is mPower from Multimedia Design Corp. mPower is a multimedia authoring package that allows instructors to make slides and charts without programming or using complex icons. Contact: PRC Inc., McLean, VA; (800) 441-0670. <p><strong>CP3 Kiosk System</strong><br>The College Publishers Preview Plus Kiosk System (CP3) is an interactive CD-ROMbased preview and demonstration device for electronic course materials. CP3 enables instructors and students to preview all CD-ROM-based products located within a bookstore. The system is comprised of an IBM PC that includes speakers utilizing CP3's digital voice technology to instruct patrons in how to use the kiosk system.  The system, which is housed in a display cabinet that stands five feet tall, also includes a durable keyboard, a trackball, and numerous demo disks from companies ranging from William C. Brown Publishers to Prentice Hall.  Contact: Follett Campus Resources, River Grove, IL; (800) 322-6223. <p><img hspace=10 align=right src="images/datalift.GIF"><strong>DataLift</strong><br>Display Devices Inc. produces video projector carts and lifting devices that can hold up to 600 pounds. The latest addition is the SAM (Stationary And Maintenance) lift, which acts as a stationary mount for video projectors. The device holds up to 200 pounds and can be lowered down to 17 feet from the ceiling. The lift mechanisms in the DataLift Series hold up to 600 pounds and are designed as three-stop lifts. DataLifts can be fully retracted for storage, partially extended for viewing, and fully extended down to 32 feet. Contact: Display Devices Inc., Denver, CO; (303) 297-1754.<br clear=both><br><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/FPS.GIF"><strong>Freedom Presentation System</strong><br>The LightFolio Freedom Presentation System is a rugged carrying case for both an LCD panel and laptop computer. The System includes a backlight display for presenting materials as well as a means to contain and easily remove an LCD panel. The System can be used with many kinds of LCD projection panels including Sharp and Sayett. Contact: LightFolio Corp., Atlanta, GA; (404) 242-4005.<br clear=both> <br><strong>MLA</strong><br>Bogen Communications Inc. introduced the MLA (Modern Lectern Array) series of lecterns that combine speakers and an amplifier in a modular system. The sound quality is dispersed horizontally and includes an amplifier with a 40-Watt RMS output. The Table Top module, which can be transformed into a moveable podium system, includes a gooseneck microphone and auxiliary input, tape output, and a second microphone. Contact: Bogen Communications Inc., Ramsey, NJ; (201) 934-8500. <p><strong>MX-1 Digital Video Mixer</strong><br>The MX-1 Digital Video Mixer is a four channel mixer/switcher available from Videonics Inc. It includes more than 200 digital video effects and a built-in dual-field, infinite-window time base corrector (TBC). Other features include a preview screen that shows miniature copies of all four inputs, chroma key, audio mix, and compose features. $1,199. Contact: Videonics Inc., Campbell, CA; (800) 338-EDIT. <p><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/NEC.GIF"><strong>NEC MultiSync XM29</strong><br>The latest release in presentation monitors from NEC Technologies Inc. is the MultiSync XM29, part of the MultiSync family of multimedia monitors. Intended for small presentations, the direct-view monitor presents a 27-inch viewable image size and can connect up to four simultaneous input sources including signals from PC or Macintosh and composite PAL or NTSC video. $3,995. Contact: NEC Technologies Inc., Boxborough, MA; (800) NEC-INFO. <br clear=both><p><strong>Scan-It</strong><br>Scan-It provides instructors with the capability to incorporate multimedia presentations into a lecture. The presentation tool scans images from a computer for display on a TV screen or other NTSC device. Its features include remote control, a three-level adjustable flicker filter, and screen freeze capabilities. Scan-It requires no software and is Macintosh- and IBM PC-compatible. Contact: Digital Media Labs, San Jose, CA; (408) 577-1440. <p><img hspace=10 align=left src="images/softboard.GIF"><strong>SoftBoard</strong><br>SoftBoard is an electronic whiteboard with data communications capabilities. It can display information simultaneously on a monitor when connected to a Macintosh or Microsoft Windows computer. Users in remote locations can share information in real time and SoftBoard sessions can be saved screen by screen onto a computer file. Three models are available consisting of model 201, a wall-mounted version measuring 54 x 60 inches; model 203, which includes a rolling stand; and model 205, which is designed for office wall mounting. Pricing starts at $2,795. Contact: Microfield Graphics Inc., Beaverton, OR; (503) 626-939.<br clear=both> <p><strong>SYSTEM 8 and 10 PLUS</strong><br>Extron Electronics SYSTEM 8 and 10 PLUS are universal projector control switchers that enable bi-directional communication of large screen and data/graphics projectors. New features include audio breakaway capabilities, 300 MHz video bandwidth, Triple Action Switching with adjustable RGB to sync delay, and front-panel access to projector configuration controls. Pricing starts at $3,495. Contact: Extron Electronics, Anaheim, CA; (800) 633-9876. <p><img hspace=10 align=right src="images/touchpen.GIF"><strong>TouchPen</strong><br>TouchPen is new tool designed to be used as an input device for CRT displays. TouchPen allows input from both a finger and a pen and it can distinguish between the two. The TouchPen Kit consists of a sensor, stylus, controller, and driver. Users can incorporate annotations, drawings, data highlighting, signature capture, and handwriting recognition. $795. Contact: MicroTouch Systems Inc., Methuen, MA; (800) 642-7686.<BR CLEAR=BOTH><hr><a href="syllmart.html"><h3>Back to SyllabusMart Page</h3></a><hr><address>Copyright &copy; 1995 by Syllabus Press, Inc. All rights reserved.</address></body></html>
