iting raster images. It provides controls to adjust curves, hue, saturation, posterization level and threshold level of 24-bit raster images in any resolution and comes with built-in creative effects filters. Foreign language versions of Canvas 5 are scheduled be released soon. $600. Contact: Deneba Software, Miami, FL; (305) 596-5644. Reader Service #43<P><B>CorelDRAW 6</B><BR>Designed for Microsoft Windows 95, CorelDRAW 6 is a 32-bit graphics package that includes five fully-featured applications for illustration, photo-editing and painting, business and multimedia presentations, 3D rendering and animation. The CD-ROM consists of CorelDraw, a vector-based drawing application; Corel PHOTO-PAINT, a paint and photo retouching application; Corel PRESENTS, a new presentation application; Corel DREAM 3D, a new 3D modeling and rendering application; and Corel MOTION 3D, a new 3D animation program. $695. Contact: Corel Corp., Ottawa, Ont., Canada; (613) 728-8200. Reader Service #44<P><B>Dabbler 2</B><BR>Dabbler 2 for Windows and Macintosh is a paint and draw CD-ROM application. It incorporates flipbook animation, which lets users animate their creations and use multimedia-based art tutors. The flipbook creations can be exported as QuickTime or Video for Windows movies or printed out as physical flipbooks on a printer. $69. Contact: Fractal Design Corp., Aptos, CA; (800) 297-2665. Reader Service #45<P><B>Fractal Design Poser</B><BR>Fractal Design Poser is an application for creating human forms for graphics design, illustration, multimedia and 3D composition. The modeling and rendering application allows users to create a variety of human figures that can be posed and rendered with surface textures and multiple lights. $199. Contact: Fractal Design Corp., Aptos, CA; (800) 297-2665. Reader Service #46<P><IMG SRC="images/freestudio.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>FreeHand Graphics Studio 2.0 </B><BR>FreeHand Graphics Studio is an integrated suite of tools for digital design and illustration, image editing, 3D design, font creation, and Internet publishing. Included are four graphic design programs for the Macintosh and Windows platforms: FreeHand, Extreme 3D, Fontographer and Macromedia xRes, which is a tool for editing high-resolution images to FreeHand Graphics Studio. $699. Contact: Macromedia, San Francisco, CA; (800) 326-2128. Reader Service #47<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>Infini-D 3.0</B><BR>Infini-D is a 3D graphics tool with integrated modeling and animation features. Users can apply multiple varying shapes along a single path, enabling the production of sophisticated objects. Features include animatable spline models, extended animation sequencer, and precise velocity control. Contact: Specular International, Amherst, MA; (413) 253-3100. Reader Service #48<P><B>Macromedia Animation Studio</B><BR>From the Random House New Media Series, this book and CD-ROM package is a guide to learning desktop animation using Macromedia Director, MacroModel, and other applications. The CD-ROM includes animated, interactive tutorials, clip media, and demos of products. $45. Contact: Random House New Media, New York, NY; (212) 751-751-2600. Reader Service #49<P><B>MacroModel </B><BR>This 3D modeling application incorporates CAD-accurate, spline-based tool for creating 3D models from 2D objects. It provides accuracy in 15 decimal places and includes advanced 3D snapping features for precise placement of points and objects. MacroModel supports identical modeling environments for Macintosh and Windows. Contact: Macromedia Inc., San Francisco, CA; (415) 252-2000. Reader Service #50<P><B>MediaPaint </B><BR>MediaPaint is a special-effects and painting application designed for digital video. Users can add special effects to QuickTime movies without altering the original file. Paint can be applied to a movie or image and once applied, paint can be modified to change sharpness and other characteristics. In addition, paint can be applied automatically to all frames of a movie. It includes particle systems, chroma key, and time-based filtering. Contact: Strata Inc., St. George, UT; (801) 628-5218. Reader Service #51<P><B>MeshPaint 3D</B><BR> MeshPaint 3D allows the user to paint directly on 3D objects with the color contoured, as opposed to applying textures to a surface. A Zoom in and out feature provides the user with control for detail, and tools include stamps, brush tips, and colors. Objects are first shown in a wireframe form in which the user can then adjust rotation and size to begin painting. Contact: Positron Publishing Inc., Omaha, NE; (402) 493-6280. Reader Service #52<P><IMG SRC="images/raydream.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>Ray Dream Studio </B><BR>Ray Dream Studio consists of four components on one CD-ROM: Ray Dream Designer 4, a 3D illustration program for creating full-color, high-resolution 3D images; Ray Dream Animator, an extension to Designer incorporating animation tools such as Inverse Kinematics, Object Behaviors, and more; Dream Models, a component containing more than 500 fully-textured models; and the Extensions Tool Kit, which is documentation describing the API for creating product extensions and plug-ins. $499. Contact: Ray Dream Inc., Mtn. View, CA; (415) 960-0768. Reader Service #53<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>RIO Animator</B><BR>RIO Animator is an add-on module to RIO, the object-oriented, vector-based illustration and image processing program. RIO Animator creates 2D, key-frame animations. Users can combine the two products to create scanned or video-capture images with vector-based text and objects to create a basic scene that can then be manipulated for animation sequences. Contact: AT&T Multimedia Software Solutions, Maitland, FL; (800) 448-6727. Reader Service #54<P><B>SmartSketch</B><BR>SmartSketch for Windows and Macintosh is a drawing program that can produce high-resolution drawings. It incorporates painting functionality, shape recognition for smoothing lines and correcting mistakes, and an eraser feature to remove portions of a drawing. In addition, more than 500 clip art images and eight interactive tutorials are also included. $50. Contact: FutureWave Software Inc., San Diego, CA; (800) 619-6193. Reader Service #55<P><IMG SRC="images/stdioblitz.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>StudioPro Blitz </B><BR>StudioPro Blitz is a 3D software product that incorporates full support for QuickDraw 3D, which allows users to manipulate and move rendered objects directly, rather than just as wireframes or bounding boxes. In addition, the CD-ROM includes built-in support for the Virtual Reality Modeling Language (VRML) for authoring on the World Wide Web. Contact: Strata Inc., St. George, UT; (801) 628-5218. Reader Service #56<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>trueSpace 2</B><BR>Caligari Corp.'s trueSpace for Windows is an application that creates 3D graphics. The software offers organic modeling, photorealistic ray-tracing, and broadcast-quality animation. Users can work in full 3D perspective to shape objects as if working in clay and interact in real time. $795. Contact: Caligari Corp., Mtn. View, CA; (415) 390-9600. Reader Service #57<P><B>StrataVision 3d</B><BR>This application from Strata Inc. features 3D modeling, rendering, and animation software. Capabilities include boolean modeling, power extensions including skin, unskin, and sweep, and RenderScript, a renderer that supports photorealistic textures and lighting and can scale images to any size. $695. Contact: Strata Inc., St. George, UT; (801) 628-5218. Reader Service #58<P><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><P><FONT SIZE=5>Graphics and Visualization for Data Display</FONT><P><B>GraphiC 7.1</B><BR>GraphiC is a plotting and graphics software package incorporating 3D charts, plots, and graphs. The application comes with several enhancements including the capability for users to create and manage their own windows. Contact: Scientific Endeavors Corp., Kingston, TN; (800) 998-1571. Reader Service #59<P><IMG SRC="images/graphcee.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>KaleidaGraph</B><BR>KaleidaGraph is a data analysis and graphing package for the Macintosh and Power Macintosh. It includes 16 different plot types and is capable of handling 32,000 points per column. $249. Contact: Synergy Software, Reading, PA; (610) 779-0522. Reader Service #60<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><IMG SRC="images/hrvrdxl.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>Harvard ChartXL</B><BR>Harvard ChartXL is a data charting application enabling visual analysis of spreadsheet data. It includes 2 and 3D chart types with mathematical and "what-if" analysis tools. The statistical charting feature offers 48 chart types with some that automatically calculate data and generate a final chart. Contact: SPC Software Publishing, Santa Clara, CA; (800) 234-2500. Reader Service #61<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>Harvard Graphics</B><BR>Harvard Graphics features pie, bar, column, area, line, radar, overlapped, and multiple charts. It includes drawing, painting, and bitmapped tools as well as clip art, templates, and transition effects including branches. It supports TrueType fonts, PostScript, TIFF, PCX, CGM, WMF, EPS, PICT, BMP, GIF,  and DRW, Adobe Illustrator, and WPG formats. $595 DOS; $395 Windows. Contact: SPC Software Publishing, Santa Clara, CA; (800) 234-2500. Reader Service #62<P><IMG SRC="images/spyslicer.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>Spyglass Slicer </B><BR>Spyglass Slicer is a volumetric data analysis tool that is capable of reading a variety of data and image formats. The application uses ray tracing to render data as volumes, slices, or isosurfaces. With full control of alpha values users can make any object or data value transparent, translucent, or opaque for advanced volumetric rendering. $695. Contact: Fortner Reasearch, Sterling, VA; (703) 478-0181. Reader Service #63<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><IMG SRC="images/tecplot.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right><B>TECPLOT</B><BR>TECPLOT is data visualization and plotting software for graphs ranging from XY plots to 3D volumetric visualization. The interactive, menu-driven 32-bit data visualization and plotting program has additional capabilities when added to 3DV, an optional extension. Users can create and display 3D stream lines and stream ribbons as well as support for 3D gridding and interpolation from randomly ordered data. Pricing starts at $649. Contact: Amtec Engineering Inc., Bellevue, WA; (206) 827-3304. Reader Service #64<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><p><FONT SIZE=5>Scientific Visualization and Courseware</FONT><P><B>ALCHEMY III </B><BR>ALCHEMY III is an interactive 3D molecular visualization tool. It includes spacefill, ball & stick, wireframe, cylinders, and fitting and docking for new compound exploration. Students can transfer the 3D images to ChemPrint, which is a chemistry drawing program with custom templates. In addition, students can transfer 2D images to ALCHEMY for 3D analysis. $795 (DOS and Windows); $950 (Macintosh). Contact: Tripos, St. Louis, MO; (800) 323-2960. Reader Service #65<P><B>CS ChemOffice 3.0</B><BR>CS ChemOffice is a suite of software including drawing and modeling tools. Included are ChemDraw, a chemistry drawing program; Chem3D Pro, a molecular modeling and analysis application, real-time animation, and automatic conversion to 3D; and ChemFinder Pro, a productivity tool for organizing information. $1,295 list; $599 academic. Contact: CambridgeSoft Corp., Cambridge, MA; (800) 315-7300. Reader Service #66<P><B>HyperChem</B><BR>HyperChem is an integrated and flexible molecular modeling application for Windows. The application includes tools for studying and predicting chemical properties. Simulations include chemical properties such as energy, heat of formation, and others. Contact: HyperCube Inc., Waterloo, Ont., Canada; (800) 960-1871. Reader Service #67<P><IMG SRC="images/molecules.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT><B>Molecules-3D </B><BR>With Molecules-3D, users can accurately visualize, analyze, and document research in chemistry. The application has four major features: the 3D Structure Library is an assortment of 3D models that can be customized or expanded; chemVISAGE allows users to access 3D structure visualization and rendering capabilities; Coach Lewis is a structured introduction to Lewis diagrams; and 3D Model Builder includes a graphical builder, an interactive visual editor, 3D syntax checker, and 3D cleanup for structure optimizations. Contact: Molecular Arts Corp., Anaheim, CA; (714) 634-8100. Reader  Service #68<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>VESPRTutor</B><BR>VESPRTutor is a study aid for visualizing 3D molecular structures. The application incorporates graphics and animation to display spatial relationships in true perspective. It includes MacMolecule, which allows display of 3D color models of molecules and interactive rotation. $39. Contact: Intellimation, Santa Barbara, CA; (800) 346-8355. Reader Service #69<P><B>Spatial Ware: Principles of Perspective</B><BR>Spatial Ware: Principles of Perspective is interactive, 3D animated software designed to teach students 3D visualization skills for mechanical and freehand drawing. It illustrates the six principles of perspective drawing: rectangular space, eye-level line, vanishing lines, vanishing points, inclined planes, and perspective types. $39. Contact: Intellimation, Santa Barbara, CA; (800) 346-8355. Reader Service #70<P><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><P><FONT SIZE=5>Drawing Tablets</FONT><P><B>ArtPad II</B><BR>Wacom's ArtPad II and Erasing UltraPen create an art studio on the desktop. The active area of the tablet's dimensions is 4" x 5" and enables editing electronic images and production of full-color illustration. The UltraPen is plug-and-play and includes 256 pressure levels. Contact: Wacom Technology Corp., Vancouver, WA; (360) 750-8882. Reader Service #71<P><B>DrawingSlate II</B><BR>DrawingSlate II is a pressure sensitive 4 x 5-inch or 6 x 9-inch graphics tablet and pressure sensitive pen. It includes a slider bar that controls pressure sensitivity and recordable macros, allowing users to program the buttons on the pointing tool and the blocks on the tablet surface for commonly used functions. Contact: CalComp, Anaheim, CA; (800) 932-1212. Reader Service #72<P><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><P><FONT SIZE=5>Virtual Reality Applications</FONT><P><B>StrataVirtual 3d</B><BR>This virtual reality application allows users to move a scene or model using a mouse and the built-in virtual navigator. Features include camera tilt, rotation, and perspective. $299. Contact: Strata Inc., St. George UT; (801) 628-5218. Reader Service #73<P><IMG SRC="images/virtus2.gif"  HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT><B>Virtus WalkThrough Pro </B><BR>This application is a 3D modeling, visualization, and navigational tool allowing users to walk through rooms and other designs with mouse or keyboard control. Users can incorporate scanned-in photographs and QuickTime movies, as well as use perspective-correct texture mapping. $495. Contact: Virtus Corp., Cary, NC; (800) 847-8871. Reader Service #74<BR><BR CLEAR = ALL><BR><B>Virtus VR</B><P>Virtus VR allows users to create 3D worlds with drag-and-drop functionality. It includes pre-built images that can be dropped into 2D designs that will render instantly in a 3D window. $99. Contact: Virtus Corp., Cary, NC; (800) 847-8871. Reader Service #75 <P><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT><P><FONT SIZE=5>Visualization for Mapping</FONT><P><B>ArcView Version 2</B><BR>ArcView Version 2 is a desktop mapping and Geographical Information Systems (GIS) software tool for visualization of data. The application can be used to view, query, and produce maps from existing GIS data. ArcView is available for Macintosh, PC-compatibles, and a variety of UNIX and OpenVMS workstations. Contact: ESRI, Redlands, CA; (909) 793-2853. Reader Service #76<P><HR><P><MENU><FONT SIZE=5>Back to <A HREF="syllmart.html">SyllabusMart</A></FONT></MENU><P><hr><address>Copyright &copy; 1996  Syllabus Press, Inc. All rights reserved.</address></BODY></HTML>
