<TITLE>November / December '96 Buyer's Guide</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Thursday, August 1, 1996  12:11 PM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6>Telecommunications and the Internet</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER>A Buyer's Guide</CENTER></FONT>
<p>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<CENTER>A guide to the latest tools for connecting the campus to the Internet and networked information resources</CENTER>
<p>
<CENTER><A HREF="RS_list.html">click</A> here for free product information</CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=5>Desktop Publishing and Multimedia Authoring Tools</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Communication Software</FONT>
<P>
<B>Arial E-Mail Merge</B><BR>
Arial E-Mail Merge works by reading records from any database that supports comma-delimited or tab-delimited formats such as Microsoft Access, dBase, Paradox, or FoxPro. It combines data with a message file template to create a series of customized e-mails. The e-mail inserts information from the database (up to 256 fields can be used), enabling the sender to address the e-mail recipient by name and include important details. Contact: Arial Software, Portland OR; (503) 646-4515. Reader Service #50
<P>
<B>CommanSpace</B><BR>
CommanSpace, ideal for distance learning programs, is collaborative writing groupware for Windows and Macintosh. Features include a column-based interface that allows multiple parties to create columns adjacent to a document for making written or voice annotations; multiple workspaces for tracking drafts of complex documents; and multiple, real-time conferencing. CourseMap, a program designed to work with CommanSpace, is a document management system that organizes the electronic exchange of syllabi, handouts, assignments, and class bulletins. Contact: Sixth Floor Media, Boston, MA; (800) 565-6247. Reader Service #51
<P>
<B>LearningSpace</B><BR>
The Lotus Notes-based LearningSpace is a collaborative distance learning solution that gives academic institutions a flexible, cost-effective way to educate students online and provide personal feedback from instructors. The heart of the program consists of five interactive databases that enable users to collaborate on problem-solving activities, debates, discussions, and exercises. Contact: Lotus Development Corp., Cambridge, MA; (800) 346-6409. Reader Service #52 
<P>
<B>MailKeeper</B><BR>
MailKeeper is mail management software that stores and retrieves information such as e-mail, notes, text clippings, and electronic addresses. MailKeeper allows the user to leave open an application and go online simultaneously. MailKeeper uses a proprietary new technology called Guided Information Access (GIA), which prepares, stores, retrieves, and organizes information. Contact: NISUS Software Inc, Solana Beach, CA; (619) 481-1477. Reader Service #53
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Hardware</FONT>
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/prspctr.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right>
<B>Prospector WebStation </B><BR>
The Prospector WebStation allows users to navigate the Web with a  a touch screen. Developed with Spyglass, Inc., the Prospector enables organizations to leverage their investments in existing Web sites by showcasing them in WebStations in the form of kiosks or tabletop touch monitors. A surfcontrol feature confines users to specific Web sites. Prospector can also be used with an intranet, allowing employees or students to receive up-to-date information using the touchscreen. Contact: MicroTouch Systems, Inc., Methuen, MA; (888) 932-7828. Reader Service #54
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<br>
<IMG SRC="images/smrtbrd.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=0 ALIGN=right>
<B>SMART Board </B><BR>
This interactive, electronic whiteboard, which measures 4' x 3,' can be used to deliver lectures and give multimedia presentations in classrooms. By adding an LCD projector to the SMART Board, an instructor can press on the Board to control any software application or draw in electronic ink on top of projected computer images. Included with the SMART Board are software and a collection of pen tools. SMART Board is compatible with Windows and Macintosh. Contact: SMART Technologies Inc., Calgary, Alberta, Canada; (403) 245-0333. Reader Service #55 
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<BR>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Internet and Intranet Applications</FONT>
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/asksam.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT>
<B>askSam Web Publisher</B><BR>
A product designed to simplify publishing documents and databases on the Internet and intranets, askSam Web Publisher allows the user to create new documents or import existing documents without knowledge of HTML. It also allows users to include a full-text search engine to search a database or an entire Web site. askSam Web publisher is a CGI (Common Gateway Interface) application that can run on Windows NT and Windows 95. $1,495. Contact: askSam Systems, Perry, FL; (800) 800-1997. Reader Service #56
<P>
<B>IntraBuilder</B><BR>
IntraBuilder is a line of live data-driven Intranet applications development suites for Windows NT and Windows 95 that includes the bundling of the Netscape FastTrack Web server and Navigator Gold internet client software. It is available in three configurations: IntraBuilder, designed for small workgroups; IntraBuilder Professional, designed for high-volume intranets; and IntraBuilder Client/Server, which offers all of the Professional version features, plus access to all corporate databases. Contact: Borland International Inc., Scotts Valley, CA; (408) 431-1064. Reader Service #57
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/ntwrkmci.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT>
<B>networkMCI WebMaker </B><BR>
The networkMCI WebMaker is an all-in-one package of Internet hardware, software, access services, and technical support to assist schools and universities in designing professional-looking WWW sites. WebMaker can function as an Internet access server and support e-mail. Contact: MCI Corp., San Francisco, CA; 1-800-644-NEWS. Reader Service #58
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<BR>
<B>Statisphere</B><BR>
The Statisphere is a Web traffic analyzer that reports on who is visiting a Web site and what content he or she is reading. The Statisphere is capable of reporting on how many users visit a site on intranets or the Internet during a given day, week, or month. The software also determines which pages are the most popular, what sites have referred visitors, and when peak traffic times occur. Running on Windows 95 or Windows NT, 32-bit Statisphere can analyze ASCII log files for Windows, UNIX and Macintosh Web servers. $399. Contact: O'Reilly & Associates, Inc., Sebastopol, CA; (800) 998-9938. Reader Service #59
<P>
<B>ToolBook II Librarian</B><BR>
The ToolBook II Librarian is a course management system designed  specifically for managing the delivery of training and education over the Internet. Students are able to access Internet-based courseware and administrators can track and record student progress, test results, and other feedback. It runs in cooperation with a Web server, available for both Windows NT and Solaris UNIX. Contact: Asymetrix Corp., Bellevue, WA; (800) 448-6543. Reader Service #60
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Network Productivity Tools</FONT>
<P>
<B>Apple Network Admistrator Toolkit</B><BR>
This new suite of products gives network administrators of Macintosh systems the capability to set security access privileges for files and applications, control computing and print resources, distribute applications, and manage group and user lists from a central workstation. The products include At Ease for WorkGroups 4.0, Apple Network Assistant, and Apple User and Group Manager. Pricing starts at $599 for a 10-pack license. Contact: Claris Corp., Santa Clara, CA; (408) 987-7000. Reader Ser-vice #61
<P>
<B>CLASSNET Interactive Control System</B><BR>
 As part of the CLASSNET Interactive Control System for computer classrooms, CLASSNET CardRoom installs directly into the user's computer, eliminating the need for an external student or teacher interface unit. CLASSNET Lite consists of a PCB, which is installed in both student's and instructor's CPUs, then connected via a daisy-chain using high-resolution transmission cable. Contact: Minicom USA, Holland MI; (800) 922-8020. Reader Service #62
<P>
<B>COMMBLASTER Multi-Modem PCI Card</B><BR>
The COMMBLASTER is a multi-modem communications solution for Internet servers and bulletin board systems (BBS).  It can house up to eight modems that are connected to the high-speed PCI bus via a single PCI interface chip ensuring maximum data rates in excess of conventional externally connected serial port modems. Contact: Second Wave Inc., Austin, TX; (512) 329-9283. Reader Service #63
<P>
<B>Compaq Netelligent Management Software Version 1.0</B><BR>
Compaq Netelligent Management Software, Version 1.0, is a SNMP-based network management application. Compaq Netelligent is networking product, simplifies the installation and configuration of Netelligent products, and reduces support and maintenance costs by monitoring the networking devices, alerting the user of a network fault or performance problem. Contact: Compaq Computer Corp., Houston, TX; (800) 544-5255. Reader Service #64
<P>
<B>CyberSWITCH 100 Series</B><BR>
The CyberSWITCH 100 Series provides users with remote connectivity to central LAN/WAN resources and the Internet. It offers users high-speed ISDN access and is available in six different models. The CyberSWITCH will compress and transfer data over an ISDN line at rates up to 512 Kbps per channel to move intense graphic images and data including X-Rays, CAD drawings, and other large files. Contact: Cabletron Systems Inc., Rochester, NH; (603) 332-9400. Reader Service #65
<P>
<B>ForeView 4.0</B><BR>
ForeView Network Management Software 4.0 is a suite of network management applications for multi-vendor ATM networks. New features include a graphical user interface (GUI) for the configuration and management of virtual LANs (VLANS). VLAN Manager is intended to provide an easy solution to network configuration and includes many drag-and-drop functions. $2,495-Windows NT and $4,995-UNIX. Contact: FORE Systems, Pittsburgh, PA; (412) 722-6600. Reader Service #66
<P>
<B>HyperACCESS Pro </B><BR>
The HyperACCESS Pro for OS/2 is general purpose communication software with the remote control powers of Hilgraeve's KopyKat remote control package. It allows users to access bulletin board systems (BBS), Internet telnet sites, online services, and host computers; plus remote control of OS/2 PCs. Its 32-bit multichannel technology allows users to simultaneously transfer files, use remote control, and chat. This product supports a wide variety of modems (about 600 models) and allows users to communicate through the Internet or TCP/IP, NetBIOS, or SPX/IPX networks. $199. Contact: Hilgraeve Inc., Monroe, MI; (800) 826-2760. Reader Service #67
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/iroom.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT>
<B>iRoom</B><BR>
The iRoom is a network control systems that accommodates educational institutions that need to control equipment functions from the classroom and two-way communications with the media center. The iRoom line of control systems to control presentation technology includes video projectors, VCRs, CD-I players, lighting, audio systems, power screens, and document cameras. Contact: ADCOM Inc., Toronto, Ontario, Canada; (415) 251-3355. Reader Service #68
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<BR>
<B>LAN Commander</B><BR>
LAN Commander is a software package that allows users to distribute software, remotely-control networked Macintosh computers, and gather system and software configuration information. LAN Commander has several uses in the classroom, such as giving the instructor the capability to quit all of the applications the last class used, then launch a different set for the next class. An instructor can also opt to lock keyboards and mice for complete attention. Contact: Power On Software, Sherrodsville, OH; (800) 344-9160. Reader Service #81
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/netmod.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right>
<B>NetMod</B><BR>
Developed by the University of Michigan's Center for Information Technology Integration, NetMod is a network-capacity planning tool that generates and evaluates complex network architectures. It does number crunching to eliminate the rigor of calculations. NetMod also applies mathematical (questioning) models that use closed-form analytical techniques to calculate component utilization, throughput, and packet delays. Contact: University of Michigan Software Technology Management Office, Ann Arbor, MI; (313) 936-0435. Reader Service #69
<BR CLEAR = ALL>
<BR>
<B>ShivaIntegrator </B><BR>
ShivaIntegrator is a family of ISDN remote access systems designed to combine on-demand ISDN networking with a host of tariff management and WAN cost-saving features. The ShivaIntegrator 500 is a central site concentrator that supports Primary Rate ISDN with up to 46 simultaneous connections to remote locations, and V35 interface for leased line connection. Contact: Shiva Corp., Burlington, MA; (800) 977-4482. Reader Service #70
<P>
<B>V-Net 3</B><BR>
V-Net 3 is made for CBT facilities to give instructors the power to monitor and control any computer inside the facility. V-Net can route high-resolution computer video signals from any workstation to any other. The instructor is able to view video from any student's workstation, scan through the class, share the work of one student with the entire class, or blank student monitors for immediate attention. Signals can also be routed to a large-screen data display. Optional V-Net features include student buttons, intercom, and stereo audio sharing. Contact: Inline Inc., La Habra, CA; (800) 882-7117. Reader Service #71
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>

<FONT SIZE=5>Video Conferencing Software and Hardware</FONT>
<P>
<B>Being There 3.0</B><BR>
Being There 3.0 is a video conferencing and file-sharing software for the Macintosh. Designed for any kind of connection between two computers, it features object- based whiteboarding, drag and drop file transfer, application window sharing and H.320 compatibility. Contact: Intelligence at Large Inc., Philadelphia, PA; (215) 387-6002. Reader Service #72
<P>
<B>Enhanced CU-SeeMe</B><BR>
Enhanced CU-SeeMe is desktop video conferencing software for real-time person-to-person or group conferencing. This software runs on both Windows and Macintosh computers and offers full-color video, audio, chat window, and whiteboard communications. CU-SeeMe uses a unique protocol to manage, receive, and rebroadcast video and audio data. The protocol was developed specifically for TCP/IP networks and the Internet. Contact: White Pine Software Inc., Nashua, NH; (800) 241-7463. Reader Service #73
<P>
<B>SMART 2000 Conferencing </B><BR>
SMART 2000 Conferencing software for distance learning gives teachers and students in up to 64 different locations the capability to share and annotate images and Windows applications in real-time over phonelines, ISDN, or LANs/WANs. Lab packs and site licensing are available. Contact: SMART Technologies Inc., Calgary, Alberta, Canada; (403) 245-0333. Reader Service #74
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/tchngpro.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=LEFT>
<B>Teaching Pro 5000</B><BR>
The Teaching Pro 5000 system is a portable, fully integrated distance learning system developed to assist teaching professionals in effective delivery of lesson plans to students locally and in remote locations. The user is able to conduct class with a two-way, interactive voice, with video and data communications simulating same- room lesson plan delivery through the use of onboard multimedia tools and peripherals. This system  features an instructor- controlled camera, 33mm slide-to-video converter, fax copier/printer, and touch- screen control of all system functions. Contact: NEC America, Inc., Irving, TX; (800) TEAM-NEC. Reader Service #75
<P>
<HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=4 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>Servers</FONT>
<P>
<B>AMX Synergy Client/Server</B><BR>
The AMX Synergy Client/Server is a resource management tool that provides a solution for instructor and student access to shared educational resources. Synergy Client software connects people to the Server over a local area network, a wide area network, or the Internet. The user can schedule media and other resources on a particular day or period of time to prevent conflicts for media and source availability. The program has several features such as a library search for media titles, broadcast channels, or physical items. The user can also view future, current, and past events, as well as control the presentation with two on-screen control panels. Contact: AMX Corp., Dallas, Texas; (800) 222-0193. Reader Service #76
<P>
<B>CLI Multimedia Conference Server</B><BR>
The CLI Multimedia Conference Server (MCS) delivers expanded network connectivity options, and enhanced conference management and diagnostic capabilities in a multi-site environment. A Continuous Presence feature allows instructors to simultaneously project images of students and other instructors into equal quadrants enabling all participants to see, hear, and interact with each other without switching from site to site. Contact: CLI, San Jose, CA; (408) 428-6735. Reader Service #77
<P>
<B>neT.120 </B><BR>
The neT.120 Conference Server allows real-time, multi-point data conferencing on the Internet and corporate intranets. It is a standards-based, software-only server product for hosting multi-point conferences. Any user with an HTML browser can participate in a conference. Contact: DataBeam Corp., Lexington, KY; 
(606) 245-3500. Reader Service #78
<P>
<IMG SRC="images/netra.gif"ALT="graphic"  VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 ALIGN=right>
<B>Netra NFS Server</B><BR>
The Netra NFS Server simplifies the job of network administration through a device-independent HTML-based GUI interface. The administrator can manage the system from any PC, Macintosh, or UNIX system on the network by using a familiar Web browser interface. With a user/password check and the capability to restrict access to a limited client set, the Netra NFS Server provides secure remote network administration. Contact: Sun Microsystems Computer Co., Mountain View, CA;  (415) 786-7737. Reader Service #79
<BR CLEAR = ALL>

<BR>
<B>WebSite PRO for Teachers</B><BR>
The WebSite PRO for Teachers is an expanded server kit tailored for educators in K-12 and higher education. It includes the complete commercial WebSite Professional package and a copy of The Whole Internet for Windows 95, by Ed Krol. Featuring cryptographic security, WebSite PRO also includes remote administration and virtual servers for creating multiple home pages. The application is available for Windows NT and Windows 95. $149. Contact: O'Reilly & Associates, Inc., Sebastopol, CA; (800) 998-9938. Reader Service #80
<P>
